Review Text: Really disappointed for the dishes‚Ä¶. Not athletic Sichuan food. Especially the maoxuewang. The restaurant play on words. They change the ÊØõ to ÂÜí, which is not respect the spirit of Sze Chuan Food!

Excellent meal in a warm atmosphere! The space feels intimate and warm despite it being a high ceiling, concrete floored barn‚Ä¶ great design. Also manages to feel casual and elegant at the same time, with both the design and ambience. The meal was excellent. We shared the chopped salad, filet mignon with horseradish which was cooked perfectly and the red wine glaze is an excellent touch, the robuchon mashed potatoes and mushrooms which were both excellent sides, the crab spaghetti which has a spice to it and a ton of perfectly cooked crab, and the pecan streusel carrot cake. Everything was amazing, would recommend every dish. Worth the trip from the city up to Evanston for a meal that rivals the best steakhouses in Chicago, including all those hard to get resy Hogsalt restaurants.
Best burger in Evanston
Second best burger in Evanston
Good service, beautiful interior but the food, unfortunately, wasn‚Äôt very good.

Really great room! 

Relatively
 small and clubby feel with comfortable leather booths, dark paneling, 
and well-planned lighting. Very welcoming friendly vibe. Cozy, clubby 
bar across the hall. Restrooms were well above average.

Mmmmmmmmmmm!!! That's the sound of me eating the best salad in the universe, the "New School Chicken Salad" from Picnic. The combination of the cheese, grapes, chicken, greens, candied nuts, pickled shallots, etc. is incredible. See the before and after photos attached to this review. Tied with the salad is the lemon tart. W-O-W. The service is very good (it is a take-out establishment, but the comfy couch and chair plus the beautiful d√©cor make it a very pleasant place to wait for your meal to be prepared) and the prices are more than reasonable. I can hardly wait to come back again and try something else!
Small place with great Italian food. LARGE portions and reasonable prices and great staff Easy to park . Has been around for at least 25 years in different locations and Venues.

We just had a fabulous dining experience! From the moment we walked in we were greeted with warmth. The food and service was all excellent. We loved everything we ordered . We started with pink pomelo salad and Crispy Brussels sprouts. Then we got two main dishes to round out our meal. The short ribs and shrimp noodles were so good! I highly recommend going to this very special Thai restaurant. We can‚Äôt wait to go back. I wish I took photos of everything we ate.

I knew good Steak n Shakes could exist. It literally feels chef driven right now. I‚Äôm now incredibly addicted to the triple steak burger. The way they smash the burger thin so it becomes a crispy meat sheet on the edges üíÅüèΩ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è It is a line worth waiting it every time.
This place is awesome! The crepes and pastry are delicious. I'm so happy we found it. It is so far the best french bakery place we've found. The hot chocolate was supreme BTW
AVOID. Every employee here has a s*** attitude. They take it out on the customers with their eye rolls and under breath comments.

I've found myself eating from here several times just out of convenience and wanting a snack, but I've always felt like they could be more flavorful. I've tried the spinach & cheese, caramelized onion, bbq chicken, Mac and cheese and a few more and they could definitely be better. They're pretty good to just put something on your stomach, but for the price...I'd opt for something else.

Best described as "contemporary", NaKorn serves up Thai flavors without the comfort.
Wasn't expecting to see ginger bourbon popcorn chicken on the appetizer list but it wasnt bad. Tapioca pearl crackers with minced chicken and shrimp relish was the highlight of my meal - simple with complex flavors and well portioned.
Both the coconut poached seafood and coconut curry braised chicken were tasty, but I would've been just as happy if not happier with Tom Yum Gung and Panang Gai.
Mildly disappointed the dessert options didnt include Kao Niew Ma Muang. The chocolate mousse was okay.
It's the kind of place you'd go to experience something different because of the curb appeal, but doesn't inspire me to come back.

The best chirashi bowl ever. Ordered on door dash but will need to dine in sometime. Every thing was fresh and proportions were huge. Uni is very hit & miss but this place was a hit!!!! Authentic Japanese for sure please check em out

Food is excellent. I had a bbq burger and it was fantastic. The fries are fresh and no residual oils as if it was air fried. Place is clean and staff was friendly. The price commensurate with location and type of food, but much more healthier in my opinion.

The Mutt (pictured above) included 1/2 pork hot link, 2 smoked chicken wings, and 1/2 lb of rib tips. The meat was served on a bed of fries and comes with a slice of bread. The fries and bread pair well with the bbq sauce from the meat. The meat was moist and had a slight smoky flavor. There's a lot of food. I would recommend Hecky's if you're hungry for flavorful barbecue.

My family loves Nepalese/Indian cuisine and we have never been pleased with the options in the North Shore/Evanston area. We stumbled upon Taste of Nepal in our search for take out tonight and didn‚Äôt realize it was brand new! We‚Äôre so happy we tried it because everything tasted AMAZING. So flavorful and delicious. Portions are healthy so we have leftovers for lunch tomorrow as well. Delivery was fast and friendly. Definitely recommend! We will be regulars!

Time of day makes a difference in your experience. The food is very good and it‚Äôs an easy place to sit and hang out with friends and family. But, the wait to get your food can be a while. My wife and I waited 40 minutes, on a Saturday morning, to get our food after we placed the order.

This place is EXCELLENT and I am not even a vegan or vegetarian. The burger was amazing, the fries were crispy and, most of all, the milkshake tasted real. I was pleasantly surprised. All of it is very reasonably priced.
Absolutely phenomenal. The decor is breathtaking and the food is exceptional. I can‚Äôt wait to go back! I would highly recommend the oyster mushrooms and the apple dessert (pictured).
Amazing food

Just ordered a burger here through postmates and my burger had a hair in it. I also asked for bacon in the sandwich, which they forgot to put in despite charging extra for it. Downright disgusting and disappointing, especially because this used to be a favorite place of mine.

The brisket Sandwich is absolutely amazing. Perfect flavor. Their signature barbecue sauce is perfect, as is their seasoning on the fries. I‚Äôm definitely coming back to try all the other items on the menu. Highly recommend this place.
The dishes are pretty salty, especially the cold dish. The sauce over it is too thick and salty and sweet too while the beef soup is plain and has no taste

We come to this spot whenever we are craving Indo-Chinese. The staff is always so accommodating and friendly. Their food is consistently delicious ‚Äî we love their serving sizes and it‚Äôs nice to order a lot and share as a group. Their fried rice is iconic and made so well! One of my favorite dishes is their Gobi Manchurian appetizer. You won‚Äôt go wrong!

This is my favorite place for coffee when I‚Äôm in Evanston. It is a French style coffee shop and small bakery. I feel like I‚Äôm transported to France every time I walk in. The latte was great with almond milk. I will be back sometime soon!

As a resident of Evanston for several years now, I‚Äôve been to this restaurant many times. The food is south Asian ( Nepali and Indian ) but more ‚ÄúAmericanized‚Äù ( read : a bit on the bland side of things )to suit the audience for the restaurant. But, it still manages to get the balance of spice and flavors for the most part. This time we had the momos, pakoras, tandoori roti and mutter paneer. Was a little bit disappointed that the paneer wasn‚Äôt as soft as it is usually. But otherwise, the food tasted good and service was quick too. I‚Äôve been to their buffet lunch ( pre covid) on several occasions and it was a great value for money. They also have a 10% wildcard discount for northwestern students.
Warm and cozy restaurant for winter dining.
Amazing tea and really chill spot. They also have Thai ice cream. Had the honey green tea and it was awesome. Nice location and easy parking in front. A lot of options on the menu from hot to cold.

Upscale Thai place with artistically plated food. Decent quality. Unfortunately not too vegetarian friendly or willing to substitute vegetables on request, which most other places do - our waiter wouldn't even ask the chef for us! So that was disappointing.

This was one of the best sushi experiences I have ever had. The signature rolls (carnival and citrus spring) were elegant, fresh, and creative. The combination of flavors was so delightful. You can tell attention goes into this food.

Great service and great, casual atmoshphere. The inside is very nice and vibrant. We ordered the rainbow roll, jalapeno poppers, and different ramen bowls. Pictured is the tantanmen. Agree with other reviews that the ramen is delicious, however I would pass on the sushi. Only complaint is that the jalapeno poppers are filled with imitation crab when the menu says raw spicy salmon. I only ordered them for the salmon inside so I was disappointed.

The icecream is just awesome and I loved their choco cones. Too bad they only allow Uber eats delivery which require you to tip the delivery guy and also pay taxes. They will be a perfect 10 once they start UberEATS pickup.
I‚Äôm SO happy, finally some great authentic flavor for a Mexican restaurant in Evanston. Friendly staff and cool atmosphere. Definitely coming back.
Poor service, crowded space.
No food - only beer. What kind of restaurant doesn't serve food?
A good neighborhood Italian restaurant. A wide selection of typical choices and a few specials. Good wine selection. Oleasant family atmosphere
Amazing food
The vegetarian plate was some of the best food I‚Äôve ever had! Very generous for the price, too. And the owner (I think?) was very kind.

In a nutshell they price gouge. They charge 16.25% tax on alcohol. They charge a "supplier" fee. They bundle food, alcohol and all the misc fees and taxes together, then charge you gratuity on the entire amount, not just the food.
One of the best restaurants to provide indian food near northwestern campus
The food is delicious and prepared when it's ordered, as expected in a good restaurant of this food type.

Ordered from uber eats today 3/21/22 and ordered a sunshine grape-ade. I‚Äôve had many ade‚Äôs in the past and they‚Äôve always come carbonated with fruit syrup. As you can see I received a different drink, a sunshine pineapple tea ? Completely wrong fruit and wrong drink type, Im confused as to how this happened. Very disappointed, I had paid quite a bit for the grape-ade with %100 sugar only for a random tea to come that tasted bitter with old tapioca inside. If you do not have a product in stock please PLEASE call the customer to see what else they would like. I‚Äôm also looking at the website and the pineapple tea and grape-ade are in completely different categories as well. Giving 2 stars because the taro slush we ordered was actually correct.
My favorite boba place in Evanston

I ordered food this evening. I was quite disappointed with the portions of my Mongolian beef and the and its looked as if it was a cup of rice. The thing that Disturbed me was when I called to express my disappointment. The young lady tells me that this has been the portions size for 11 years. I have ordered food on many occasions. I have never had this happen before. So they won't have to worry this is my last time every ordered from them.

This place is nice for a brunch with the family. It‚Äôs clean and welcoming. I got a pancake sandwich, my mom got the boulder crepes, and my dad got the homestead breakfast. There was a bit of a wait to get our food and our waiter forgot to grab us our coffee creamers. They gave us two bowls in the end. And even though we were halfway through our meal they placed the bill on the table. The food was good overall but not the best.
Place is quiet. After 3 pm no dine in. When quiet food takes 20 min to order. No tables outside. Staff is nice and helpful. They stop selling slices at 3 pm
They had no seatig so we had to leave

Tapas done the right way! What a great experience. Food was phenomenal and so was the service. Everything was prepped and served very nicely, allowing us to try different things. Portions are perfect for two people, and they aren‚Äôt overpriced. Loved it and will go back.

I liked the Thai salad but there was some uncooked rice spread throughout the salad. The buy one get one offer was great but there were too much rice and it was hard and not edible. Apart from that everything else was fine. The chicken was tasty.

I found out about Elephant + Vine from one of the founders at Barn Sanctuary in Chelsea Michigan. Had to come to Chicago to see what the hype was about! The ascetic from the outside is simple and modern, you walk into a fresh environment with a super friendly, happy staff! Vanessa was my Server tonight, she recommended the In-House-made Ranch for My Tenders and made sure I wanted everything on the Delicious Crispy Brussels. I also got the Portohouse Bowl!
Very accommodating friendly and knowledgeable staff. Everything we had was top quality, and all the things we didn't made me want to chew through the glass counter to get to them.

We ate here on a Saturday evening and the food was very slow to come out. Clearly, the restaurant was understaffed given how busy they were with takeout and to-go orders. Not only was it slow, the rice in the Thai bowl was way over cooked. Overall, I think the idea of this restaurant is good but the prices are way too high for the food being average. Had high hopes for this restaurant, but would likely go somewhere else for better Vegan options in the future.

I can‚Äôt believe it took me 3 years to come here. The breakfast sandwiches, quiches, and pastries are very good. I haven‚Äôt had one of their freshly made crepes yet but will be doing that next time. Great place for a quiet breakfast.

This will be my go to place! All the ones I got were delicious! Especialy love curry chicken, bbq chicken, mushroom, chorizo!! Full of flavors, you can taste the moist and juiciness inside! The cortado was pretty good as well:)

Do not, under any circumstances, order delivery from this place. I've made the mistake of doing so multiple times from this location and not once have I ever received a correct order. If you want Chipotle, go there in person so you can make sure they don't forget half of your order.
Love the atmosphere and the food. White table cloths but laid back attitude. Warm and attentive staff. Small but cozy space.

Meh- 3.4 stars. First time visitor. I had the Mutt combo. The Rib tips were fatty, overly marbled and underwhelming. Many better choices for Rib tips. (Uptown BBQ is great) Smoky flavor but dry... Decent seasonings were not too salty. The hot links were very tasty .
Much better than Hecky's BBQ
Excellent food, excellent service. Happy to have a wonderful new sushi and ramen spot in the area! I‚Äôll be visiting again to try more menu items. Worth the visit
The cocktails are amazing! The food was sooo good. We don't have a single negative thing to say. Service was quick too. Keep up the good work!
Amazing food

The hot chocolate in this place is amazing!! I also enjoyed the strawberry crepes. It was fairly packed and only two workers, hence the four stars. However they both did an awesome job. Will definitely come back whenever I'm in Chicago.
This location is too yt washed.  The flavors are okay and the heat is extremely muted.  If you're not yt, go to the next closest location in Uptown.  They'll cook a more flavorful/heated meal for you

This used to be my favorite restaurant in town. With the new management the service and overall experience is very poor, and I‚Äôm never returning. The saving grace is the food is still good, and the waiters are polite. The wait time has gone up quiet a bit. They‚Äôre serving food in disposable containers due to COVID which would have been admirable, had been not been for the total lack of effort with the flimsy containers and poor quality cutler. Made it difficult for the waiters to serve and patrons to eat. We sent one of the dishes back since it wasn‚Äôt good (can happen to the best of chefs), only to be confronted by the unhappy owner, ruining our evening. We requested that there be no sprouts since one of our guests is pregnant, sure enough one of the dishes had sprouts. I‚Äôve celebrated major milestones at this place and was excited to see it open back up. It‚Äôs really sad to see it go down this path.
Ice cream!
Love her Oxtails. A bit spicy, but good.

Worst experience at a drive thru. They seriously argued with me over the fact that they forgot to put my chicken sandwich in my bag claiming they were sure they did. It was clearly paid for, on my receipt, but not in the bag. I realized this once I got home and since I live nearby, drove back and they asked me to go back home and bring the bag so they could see it for themselves. Ridiculous service to argue over a $4 sandwich, that I paid for. Make sure you check your bags before you leave the attitude there is all the way stupid. Haven‚Äôt been to Burger King in yrs, thanks for reminding why I don‚Äôt go.

Wow! The service from Keith Zoe and Evan was absolutely amazing. They handled so many customers with ease and so fast; they just did such an amazing job. It was a crazy Friday night with all the Northwestern kids and they had such a great rhythm going on. They were kind and polite and did such a good job. It was just like when I used to go to Kilwins in Saint Armand‚Äôs circle when I was a kid. I have been a long time customer and it‚Äôs great to see that this Evanston location has three of the best  employees I‚Äôve ever seen. I had to let you all know because honestly they deserve shout outs.

Also the ice cream is amazing and so are the cakes. My husband got me one for my birthday and it was the best cake I‚Äôve ever given. The chocolates are sooo good and all the fudge. Pace yourself if you live here. If you‚Äôre a tourist, stock up!

I recently dined at Peppercorns and was extremely disappointed with the service. The waiters were incredibly rude and unaccommodating, making for a very unpleasant dining experience. Their lack of professionalism and customer service skills made it clear that they did not value their customers. I do NOT recommend this establishment to anyone looking for a positive dining experience and would not return due to the unacceptable behavior of the wait staff.

I generally find vegetarian imitations of meat based foods to be a bit pretentious, and somewhat disingenuous. And this one did not disappoint. But the quality was excellent, and the "steak" was tasty. All in all, a better than expected experience from the point of view of a serious meat-a-saurus. We sat at an outdoor table on the sidewalk and had a very pleasant time.

Everytime I come to tomo it's a great time. I love their spicy miso ramen even though I can't handle spicy very well I'm slurping up the ramen like it's the end of the world. I also went yesterday and tried their gyoza and it was so delicious and savory
Not worth the $

I really enjoyed Clark's. I was staying at the Hilton downtown and woke up late and was looking for a spot just like this one. I enjoyed some breakfast a little after noon and it hit the spot. The people were really friendly and the food was delicious üòã They had some really good options and coffee was included in my meal. ‚òï overall it was a great experience and I recommend it.

First let me say, the salads are fantastic. My problem is when you opt for delivery and their customer service, that is when the issues start. No issues with the delivery service, it is them providing the wrong salad to the delivery driver and suggesting that YOU come back to get the right one. I gave them a second chance and they call me AFTER the driver has already picked up my food to say they forgot to add the protein? They did attempt to call the delivery service and the driver but the response was "I tried, they will provide a credit for the protein." Okay...no attempt to make it right "Next salad is on us!" or "Next protein is on us, so sorry for the inconvenience." Not once but twice there were issues. It was like "eh..we tried." Like I said the salads are good, hence the 4 stars. However, having good food means NOTHING if the service is bad. First time shame on....well, you know the rest. There will not be a third.

love this place because they sell pizza by the slice, with tons of variety including pepperoni, sausage, and spinach, plus some deep dish options. it's $5 per slice which feels a bit expensive but it really does fill you up with the greasy goodness!
Always excellent. Family meals are fantastic.

10 dollars for a tiny cup of mac n cheese. They used to give you more before, but now they‚Äôre cheap as hell. My recommendation is go to Smylie for their Mac n cheese or go to chic-fila for their bowl of Mac n cheese. It‚Äôs cheaper and you‚Äôll get more bang for your buck.
Expensive but delicious
Claire's is hands down the best West Indian food in Chicagoland! Simple, easy with a friendly vibe, you can't go wrong picking up some delicious eats from Claire's!
The chicken salad and th chicken tacos are great. The amount is very good for the price.
Amazing service! I have allergies and they are very understanding. The ice cream is good but is a little to sugary. I would definitely recommend and will come back.
Now all self service from placing your order to getting your drinks. Once your order is ready they call your name and you have to pick it up. Maybe five customers at the time I was there.

Must try!!! Coming from someone who is Korean, this place is authentic. Loved the bulgogi bibimbop which came with sides of miso soup, potatoes, and kkakdugi. I also asked for a side of kimchi when I picked up my order (which they don‚Äôt usually sell as a side, but they gave it to me for free!) Mandoo was also very good. Will definitely be back!!
Food was not bad but the place could have been more decorative. Cash section was clumsy. I would suggest to make the food more authentic.
Perfect for date night

Me and my husband were passing through town saw this cute little place, thought we would stop in. The lady there was so rude. I asked her if they served coffee she said no, ok... so then I asked her if they served any kind of tea...she said no... then I asked he if they served food...she said nothing...they husband asked to see on the end she handed him a to go menu. It was like she didn't want us there or want our business. Never in my life have I ever been treated that way.

Me and my husband were passing through town saw this cute little place, thought we would stop in. The lady there was so rude. I asked her if they served coffee she said no, ok... so then I asked her if they served any kind of tea...she said no... then I asked he if they served food...she said nothing...they husband asked to see on the end she handed him a to go menu. It was like she didn't want us there or want our business. Never in my life have I ever been treated that way.
Too much boba in the drinks, but adorable location
Delicious ramen, perfect for a cold day

Great atmosphere and great food. I had the spicy beef Ramen and the jalape√±o poppers. The Ramen was a great level of spice and the herbs were lovely. The jalape√±o peppers were fresh and the filling was tasty. Definitely will be back.

smokey inside due to poor ventilation and constantly making crepes, staff is over worked and not enough help, prices are crazy expensive... they cannot help you properly because there were only two of them.... bad bad bad. I felt sorry for girls

For me, a pescetarian, they had no fish options and the vegetarian dish was not even listed on the menu. My meat eater friends liked it but also very greasy inside and atmosphere is non existent. Take out is your best bet.
Just tried this new place. Great veg vindaloo and samosas! Nice people and accommodating for vegans. Glad to have this place in Evanston

Tasty! So glad I got the chance to check this place out, it's well worth it! If you've ever tried Pita Inn in Skokie, you're sure to love this place, too! I got steak kabobs with saffron rice, frozen mint lemonade, and for dessert I got Firnee (rosewater milk pudding). The steak was cooked perfectly and was flavorful. The saffron rice was good. The frozen mint lemonade was to die for- it's homemade and you can taste the love that goes into it! The firnee was the perfect way to end the meal. The ambiance of this restaurant is beautiful and the server we had was incredibly kind and attentive. This is a great place to sit down and have a meal and catch up with a friend or take your family out! I'll be back most definitely.

On Tuesday night we placed an online order. We arrived 3 minutes after the given pickup time. The restaurant was not busy and Northwestern students were on break. The restaurant could not find our order. It took about 10 minutes to cook our order. There was no apology for their error.
Good ambiance. Bad ratio of pasta to toppings. I had about 10 strands of pasta in my dish so I would get something else next time.

Breakfast Skillets taste great to start the day off strong. I got the Gypsy skillet and the flavors were great. May be a little heavy and salty for someone looking for a refresher, but Le Peep has a variety of other options to choose from.
Very good bubble tea place! Quick service and wide variety of drinks available, also some food like popcorn chicken, but you should mainly come here for the boba tea
The food could not have been worse. The service was impersonal and disinterested. I really like absolutely nothing about this place.

Tried to order from here twice but the staff were overwhelmed with online and in-person orders. Both times I, as well as others, had to leave. Finally got something there today, but the cappuccino was more like a latte (sad but common around here?) and the famed chocolate almond croissant was weird. The pastry was good, but the almond filling tasted odd ‚Ä¶ maybe too much flour filler? The outdoor seating was very nice. The management needs to invest in another staff person - they were overwhelmed and it looked like a really unpleasant place to work.
If I can give this place zero stars I would.

My wife and I are still new to the area and we have a few places we like to eat because we get disappointed with the lack of flavors. I decided to try this place out because of the high reviews. I should have know something was how when I placed a pick up order.

We I was speaking to the lady on the phone everything was fine until she dismisses my question on what is the most popular sauce as this is my first time ordering here. She does not acknowledge my question and just leaves me waiting so I select the last sauce.

Upon arrival it is busy, and my order should have been ready by the time I got there. I was told on the phone it would be ready in 15 mins. I immediately pay once I get there but my order wasn't given to me until 22 minutes later. Numerous people came in and grabbed their order so I do not understand why my order took 37 mins.

Once getting home and eating the food both my wife and I were dissatisfied. The mashed potato's and gravy are whatever. Literally store bought would have been better and I would have gotten more. The spaghetti had no flavor, and my wife loves spaghetti so she was super disappointed. The chicken was juicy but had no flavor and the oil they used must be old because we both were sick to our stomach. I can get better chicken at KFC and not feel sick afterwards.
I do not recommend this place to anyone. Please go elsewhere and save your money and your tummy.
We hopefully ordered for the first time this evening. We ordered two meat entrees, two vegetable dishes, papadum, samosas, two breads, plus raita, and rice.

Fonda is a lovely spot, good food! The carnitas and shrimp tacos were my favorite‚Ä¶small in size, big in flavor. You‚Äôll enjoy every bite.
The ambience is really beautiful‚Ä¶two bars and plenty of room to mingle. Perfect for parties and solid date night. The artsy light fixtures and wall piece were a win for me.

First time visiting. I'm from the south Oklahoma to Texas area. We have better expectations.When I walked in, I told them I wanted to taste the meat not the sauce. Did not ask for their bbq sauce, they asked, so, I stated go ahead and place it on the side and I might try it. Meaning do not put it on the meat. I ordered pulled chicken and some ribs. Ribs are cut into cube slices. That was a turn off, ok, meat is somewhat tasty but small bones because it's cut into cubes. Be careful and don't choke on that one. The chicken. Pfft. Bbq sauce was added. I didn't want it, told them I want meat not sauce. Told them in pounds of how much chicken, yet they made it into a sandwich. It had sauce all over the pulled chicken. Sauce is too sweet and not that good, for me, if you like sweet, you might like theirs. Not for me. They told me in the beginning or to my understanding it would not have sauce. Next, I ordered peach cobbler, it's cold, not fresh, and a lot of bread, very soft and doughy, not cook fully, I have only 3 peach slices and the entire container with lots of dough. I do not have any anticipations of going back. Complete waste of $35+. I tried to call them back but was put on direct hold. Didn't even have hospitality to ask if I had the to time to be placed on hold. Unprofessional for me.

Hands down the new best to go spot for casual drinks and great tacos in Evanston! Although clearly understaffed (expected for a new restaurant) there's no doubt that it will get better as time goes on.
Lovely family run place. Great food. Amazing soundtrack playing when we ate there on a very cold Dec 23 (Joy Division, Clash etc). Going to go more often and also order takeout.
Am Indo - Chinese place . Probably the oy one in Chicago and definitely worth a visit if you want to try the food.
Mid. First and last visit for the time being. Went for coffee with friends and ordered lunch special. Sandwich portions were small, drinks lacked flavor, not impressed overall with what was ordered.

This is an institution. I have been there dozens of times, and given how long it has existed that isn't that many times a year. I have enjoyed their regular food (not varied, but well done) and their bar food (which is available quite late, an important feature). However, the food, at the end of the day, is what costs them a star. I've had equally good presentations of "pub grub" in other places. Theirs is nothing special.
Their beer list is not broad but it is good if you like the style they are featuring (they do a great "black 'n tan"). And I have been there on several nights (though not lately) when they have had wonderful Celtic groups playing live, and clearly playing for love.
Absolutely delicious. We loved the New Year‚Äôs Eve dinner package. Everything was prepared to perfection and was a delightful dinner.
Phenomenal authentic dishes at the right price. One bite and you‚Äôll keep ordering just to taste more. From service to drinks and desserts you have to try it!
The food here is absolutely phenomenal - seafood is top quality.

Service was great. However, food was not that good.
- Goat Cheese and tomato sauce tasted like tomato soup concentrate
- Ceviche - The pieces were cut large and the taste was overwhelmingly lemon
- Roasted beets - Very tart
- Sangria and Margarita were fine
Best beer in Evanston, the joint's a little small. Right off the Main St purple.
Best bubble tea in Evanston, although Joyees is better for price value. Cash only for orders under 8 dollars. Taro milk tea and Peach Oolong with bubbles are solid choices.

Got the liquor license back so that is a plus. The menu doesn't disappoint. The spicy tofu ..the spicy chicken the sole..everything is good and I really wanted to slam this place as a former employee. But I can't.
So good and spicy too! Was really happy with how friendly the staff were. I had the eggplant in garlic sauce and the fish hot pot. Would definitely recommend and go again.

First I asked if there were any other whopper specials besides the 2 for $6. I then decided to place my order without onions, tomatoes, and pickles. I asked if I could purchase one 2 for$6 at $3 and was told I could purchase the one Whopper at $5 and change. The Spicy Miso is top notch! Spice level is about a 6 but theyll ramp it up for you. Theres flavor everywhere - youll love it. Cozy joint with a great ambiance. Awesome spot for coworkers & friends. Kudos, guys.
It's a restaurant of nice ambience and all and I do enjoy their special fish dish. But can't help think it's a bit pricey. Don't go here for brunch - it's not worth the money.
This is the best drink in town! Even better than the original Kungfu tea in Chinatown! The girls in the front always so sweet! Awesome service!

After finding out the wait at the restaurant was over an hour, because it was a Saturday night and Ramadan, my friend and I opted for another place. The manager of the restaurant flagged us down outside the restaurant and told us to give it a couple minutes. When we got back inside, there was a table waiting for us. I was enjoying my food until the manager kick out some customers. I understand that they are teens, but they purchased something, that makes them customers. And your sign at the door does say "free wifi". It's 87¬∞ outside, let the teens enjoy their soda that they where sharing, while they search the Internet. The manager had no right to kick them out as they where customers.
Google lists open time at 7:30. Staff told me they open at 8. Now it's 8:10 and the staff disappeared with no one taking orders.

I really enjoyed Clark's. I was staying at the Hilton downtown and woke up late and was looking for a spot just like this one. I enjoyed some breakfast a little after noon and it hit the spot. The people were really friendly and the food was delicious üòã They had some really good options and coffee was included in my meal. ‚òï overall it was a great experience and I recommend it.

Awesome place for bubble/milk teas, and all sorts of other fun, colorful, assorted drinks. Very fast, up-front, and direct customer service. They even have Lactaid (lactose-free milk) for lactose-intolerant individuals (look for the name 'Wow' Tea). Inside, there are two kiosks to order from if paying with a card, but if you can also order in person too at the counter.... Always popular with Northwestern students & neighborhood people alike so expect a bit of a wait, but so worth it. You will be happy you did.

Awesome Beer in Evanston and great people who work there! Highly Recommend picking up some Sketchbook Beers, my fave is Orange Door but they are all unique and worth a try! They are right across from Main Street Train Station.
Wonder atmosphere and delicious Bammee noodles! Highly recommend!!!
I always enjoy this place. Food is good, creative. Bring a pillow for your rear end, the benches are hard

This place is just an ‚Äúok‚Äù breakfast spot. The food was piping hot but lacked flavor. The service was also just ‚Äúok‚Äù. Not sure how this place has a higher star rating. I‚Äôd personally skip this place and find one of the other local spots to dine at. Maybe it was an off day for Frida‚Äôs.

It reminded me of cheesecake factory, was okay. Pork and chicken was super dry and salty in the ramen, ramen was not really worth the price(added little toppings) and flavor was like a packet ramen. appetizers weren‚Äôt good either and overall service was meh. not really worth the price, place was a 3.5/10

Easily the worst Tonkatsu I‚Äôve had. The pork in the tonkatsu was actually quite good and flavorful though, but the broth was just so unpleasant and many of the additions tasted off, such as the bamboo shoots. My egg was also wayyyy overcooked. Those ordering with me had similar thoughts about their dishes, which were Veggie and Tofu ramen, beef udon soup, and another tonkatsu.
Wonderful experience. Can't wait to return.

Came here on a Saturday evening for dinner after hearing lots of people rave about the place. The place was fairly empty when we arrived but when we asked for a booth, they were unable to accommodate. So we got seated at a table and started with some manchow soup. The soup was flavorful and good but was served without any crispy noodles (which I'm used to). I didn't really mind because it was still really good but crispy noodles never hurt.
Good food, interesting decor, lengthy Irish menu. Service a bit slow for week night.
Good restaurant for Sushi. They have good options for vegetarians.

Went to the Alcove for an 8pm dinner reservation with my partner and his parents for his ma‚Äôs birthday. The food was very good but the service was embarrassing and careless: Our server was disengaged. Twice, he walked off right as we began asking him for something. The food runner had no idea what was going on. I can‚Äôt imagine this place not having position numbers. We asked him for share plates for our salads and he forgot. Half the entrees came out and we waited about 10 minutes for the rest. Our water glasses sat empty again and again. After both first and second courses we sat with empty plates piled up as staff walked right on past. My guess is because we made an 8pm reservation, the staff were mentally checked out by that point. Not what I would expect from a restaurant like this. We‚Äôve dined here once before as a family and raved about it. Not this time. A huge let down. Memorably bad.

The food is bland. There is no salt in the food and tastes nothing. And they serve some of the store bought frozen ready to eat food(for example momos which can not be customised). Gravy is oily and bland and the naan is flavourless. Especially the buffet/platter menu is awful. Not gonna try again.

WOW. Period. Claire is an absolute sweetheart and makes every order with tons of love. She works her tail off and always wears a spicy smile. When in doubt always ask for more jerk sauce...on everything, hell get a couple extra little cups so you can put it on your eggs for breakfast & stun your guest.

I've been going to this location for a long time. The staff has always been kind and professional. My issue which occurred today was one of sanitation. I witnessed the drive thru associate take my money in cash to then provide me with my respective change in cash while proceeding to walk over to the food area and gather then bag my food. I was disgusted. Monetary forms of payment collected have exchanged hands 1000+ times which carries all sorts of germs etc. For that same person to touch my food and then hand it to me right afterward without putting on gloves or washing their hands is unacceptable and not cleanly. Management needs to address and rectify this immediately.
Spent over $20 and 40 minutes waiting for probably the worst burger I've ever had. First and definitely last time I'll be here.
I ordered Uber Eats delivery, the food was delicious, came in fresh. I ordered Chicken Biryana with Garlic Naan, it was well prepared, came in well packaged, and the food tasted great.
Have to literally go on a screen to order your food. Add and minus what you want. Then asks if you want to tip server. Then you still have to get your food.

Paid extra amount for extra spicy tofu in the wrap. Just got one small piece of tofu. The packaging was so bad it fell apart as I tried to enjoy the wrap outside on a bench. I did not give any tips by mistake. Was that the reason for this kind of service?

TL | DR it's a descent Japanese cuisine restaurant, but I cannot recommend it for sushi or specifically Omakase. Disappointing meal.

Big sign for entry here, easy to find street parking. Some Food and the service were great, but the prices were a bit steep for what it was. Decorations were strange (angry birds characters all hanging in clear partitions.

The salmon was absolutely cooked perfectly, but the plate was a bit limited in their offering with the meal. Nice helping of rice, but only 2 broccolis and 2 carrots. That was disappointing.

I found this place as Indian Dhaba.
The food was good. It was light, medium spicy and good in taste.
Quantity for each item was very less but comparatively price is also less.
Good part is thier breads are relly good. We ordered roti, parantha and naan with butter paneer, dal makhni and thali.
Thali is more than enough for one person. On top of that you can refill it without extra cost for individual with heavy diet.
I will go to this place again to try other items.

I really enjoyed Spirit Elephant so I was excited to try this place, but was disappointed. Food was fine, but my burger was missing items that were included in the description, and it was quite expensive (even for Evanston). Also, I unfortunately found a hair in my fries.
We ordered 4 dishes. Each was fine, but not as impressed as what we expected according to previous reviews. They automatically added 18% for tips.

This is the worst Korean restaurant in Chicago area. The pot was so small, and the soup is too spicy‚Ä¶ it does not fit the price. and why give me a red pen for signature????? One star for this restaurant.

Good Jerk chicken. The rum cake is absolutely delicious. Friendly service. It‚Äôs my go to for taditional Jamaican fare... not watered down or altered for American tastebuds... did I mention the rum cake???

This place deserves a 0.
Arrived to a very small line just to wait and wait because online orders came in first.
When my turn arrived, I asked for the chicken protein, and I received a half empty spoon. Asked politely and I was turned down by saying that it was 4oz even though was I got served wasn't even half of that.
Now comes the turn of the other condiments and I ask for corn and I'm told there is no more...okay ...
I'm about to pay, 4 seconds after the last fast and they just put new corn, so I ask politely again. I get turned down, my bowl is closed so I can't. Had to suggest a side cup and who seemed the manager forced this person to serve me.
Overall a very bad experience. Seems like the people at this location don't want to work and do it with a very bad attitude.
I'm not coming back again to this location
Why is all the food in Evanston so spicy?
Too spicy
Very spicy food
The meat is inedible and has too mcuh spice
apparently short staffed bc no tables were wiped clean‚Ä¶. but I appreciate the service and the food
Good food but since when do customers tip on tax? Leaves a bad taste in the mouth. Really, there are better solutions than this.
A genuine 5 star experience. We have lived in Roger‚Äôs Park for 1.5 years and we order Thai/Chinese/Asian weekly. We have tried many different restaurants and this one surpassed them all.
If you're in the mood for some truly authentic Italian cuisine, then you need to head over to Campagnola in Evanston. This place is a hidden gem, and once you try it, you'll see why.

Not just good ‚Äúfor vegan‚Äù food, but good food period! Had been looking for a place that offers plentiful vegan but also g-free options, and found the place! Elephant & Vine has a ton of food options. I ordered the Southern Comfort salad and the Gf vegan cauliflower sweet chili and bbq wings. Everything was exceptional including the limited time Pride smoothie

The first thing I noticed were the mini quiches in the display when I walked in. They have a good variety that were flavorful and my family enjoyed them.

I got the croissant sandwich which was good. The croissant was a little overbaked (dark) for my taste on the outside but still a consistent flaky croissant nonetheless.
Awesome food, fair price, amazing service and friendly staff!
The Calamari appetizer was spot on, as was the Shrimp & Crawfish Etouffee. The host and servers were all exceptional. Highly recommend!
The best burger I ever had. The service was fast. The service is great. The restaurant is spacious and clean. I'm very very happy with my whole experience at this restaurant.
They are very inconsistent with when they sell pizza by the slice.
Best fries in the area and great burgers. Perfect for quick meal on the go. We also ordered milkshakes, taste great!

BYOB, nice place in downtown Evanston. The store has an assortment of toys, license plates from all over the USA, etc. Definitely lives up to its name of Cozy! I'd highly reccomend. Staff is great! A lot of old antiques that will definitely bring back memories from your childhood!

Gave this place a third try. My first delivery order was great! Second order of a wrap was just ok. Picked up an Ele Burger and Fries today. The fries were half empty in their container and the burger, which is supposed to have cheese, did not. Employees need some training!

It‚Äôs on my way to school so I came here too more often than I should. Latte is awesome. It‚Äôs not healthy food but it just tastes good.

Not sure how this place gets such high ratings. Tried it twice and both times tea range from mediocre to just bad, and the toppings have very weird gooey texture. There are many better bubble tea places from Asian cafes in Chicago area.

fantastic experience. the environment is very warm and inviting, and the servers are super nice. i got the tuk-bulgogi soup which was delicious, and came with a ton of sides. would definitely recommend!

I noticed the prices were different from the copy of the Cross-Rhodes Rhodes menu listed on this site. When I brought it to the attention of the girl working the counter I was informed, in a very condescending tone, the the menu I was looking at was on the google site. If I wanted to see the correct pricing I would need to go directly to their site. It was apparent that the restaurant is aware of the outdated menu on this site and could update it if they wanted to. I‚Äôm so glad I‚Äôve found this place especially close to where I work. The food is spectacular. I had the tteokbokki with ramen noodles along with a can of Milkis for lunch today. I was genuinely impressed by the quality of the meal. It came with some delicious banchan on the side which I was pleasantly surprised to see.

Wow, how did I never stop in here before? It's like a little slice of European sophistication in Evanston! I had assumed that this was just a chocolate shop, but I was very, very mistaken. Horrible horrible horrible! Lady in front over charged me and got my drink wrong I got a medium instead of a large and they put boba and I didn‚Äôt want boba. They served three clients that were after me before me.I waited a long time. When I complained that my order was wrong. Lady ignored me and shrugged it off. I will never come here again and I don‚Äôt recommend to anyone.

I had the brown sugar bubble tea latte and the bobba was nice and chewy! Great texture. I had a craving for bubble tea and this was a great spot ! Staff is friendly. The place is nice and cozy. Glad it's in Evanston

The food is 3 stars but the restaurant is not honest about their service charge. This restaurant has an authentic Chinese name, but it does not has authentic Chinese food.
Quality all around. Me and the gang had a blast!
I LOVE Panino‚Äôs!! I order from the full menu frequently and always fully satisfied. Great customer service with the best pizza in town!!

The Food is Normally Very Delicious at Cross Rhodes. But on Wed - Dec 28, 2022

My personal favorites are oxtail with cabbage, jerk chicken with rice and peas, or her curried goat. The plantains will be the best you‚Äôve ever tasted!

Went during lunch. First let me say the SMELL...sooo good. They had a lunch special so sandwich and fry for about $10. I got pulled pork, very good. The bread is soft but didnt fall apart. Honestly this is the blandest pasta I‚Äôve ever eaten. I can‚Äôt speak to their other menu items but I definitely would not recommend eating their pasta. I made an online order for the build your own pasta with angel hair, alfredo, chicken, shrimp, mushrooms, and spinach‚Ä¶I was excited initially until I ate it. Literally THE blandest thing I‚Äôve eaten. No salt, pepper, garlic or any other seasoning. Paid $27 dollars through Grubhub for what‚Ä¶never again, completely disappointed.Would‚Äôve given them zero stars if I could. Dave‚Äôs Italian Kitchen, if y‚Äôall reading this PLEASE add some flavor to your pasta!

Outdoor dining was perfect and the service was even better. Very kind, friendly, accommodating, and professional. Menu read very well and was almost too good to be true. Food was good too. I don‚Äôt think the food tasted quite the way the menu represented it though. Mild in flavor if not almost flavorless. Presented well and we had a good time nonetheless.
Ok‚Ä¶ this lady has the BEST OXTAILS I HAVE EVER HAD !

Delicious! If you're hungry, the budae-jjigae is spicy and filling. The tteokbokki is sweeter but definitely also still spicy. The panchan (small dishes pictured between the larger dishes) were cool and refreshing when eating spicier main dishes.

Man, I don't necessarily know about jamaican food like I am a pro... but all I can say is this food made my day. Got the 1/4 dark with only cabbage. I will be thinking about this meal for days. So good!
Great Thai food that is beyond your typical pad thai-type dishes. Lots of great flavors! Many gluten free options. Delicious dessert. Very cool ambiance
Sooo Good!! We've ordered here often. The curry chicken and jerk chicken are aways tender and tasty.The rice and beans m,m,m so good and the Plantans are good as well..

Quick, simple, affordable, but delicious. This location is efficient and service is usually good. The lunch rush when Northwestern is in session can be a little hectic, but otherwise I have never had a bad experience here.

Walk into a dining room festooned with fancy bronze chandeliers accompanied by rosewood decor and the hostess and wait staff will greet and serve you with extreme politeness. The next dish to the table was a chickpea dish which was extremely tasty, but just a little too salty; I returned it and they offered to replace it multiple times, however by then I was stuffed and could not eat it. So this trip to Burger King started in the normal way. We entered the parking lot in the car and pulled up to the drive through. Business as usual. The pick up window is where this visit went off course. The seemingly normal guy at the window asked how many ketchup packets we wanted. How nice! Even better, he insisted on asking repeatedly exactly how many we wanted. I usually just say "a bunch" so I don't appear picky and to be quick. Very pleased to have found someone that understood that I have very specific ketchup to food ratio needs, I asked for the seven ketchup packets I required to complete my meal. We went back to work, rather eager to begin our fine meal, and horrifically find there to be nine ketchup packets. The severity of this error as how it has affected my life has haunted me since.
Really good Thai food - especially love the Basil chicken ! Very reasonable prices. BYOB.
Food wasn't worth the price tbh even with a Groupon. The scallops were old, smelled and tasted of ammonia but masked with strong flavored kimchi. I would not go back here.

The food is tasty but the half portion was laughable for the price. I don't mind paying more but i expect reasonable portions, exceptional service and a great atmosphere in return. We got none of the above. Service was average. And the atmosphere is very plain and underwhelming. Never again.
amazing bruschetta!! the bread was good but a bit too soft to spread butter.

Fabulous seafood,well,presented but definitely at the top end of the budget range.We had the 5 course set taster menu and each course was excellent.I dropped a star because the service was way to quick,we had barley finished one course before the next arrived ,this is not what you expect at this price point,probably just a staff training requirement

Ordered online and pick up. When I arrived there's only one bag near the counter. I looked at the receipt saying this doesn't look like my order. The cashier insisted this is what I ordered and said he's pretty that's what I put into the system. I was like but the name is not even minenot even my name. And he's like then there's nothing he can do cauz that's the only order. Ended up finding my bag sitting on the other shelf. So shocked about how the service was. Literally zero.
Terrible cheese blintzes

The service was fast even during peak lunch hour. The seating a bit tight given how many tables they try to squeeze in.

The apple crepes with walnut and Brie was excellent. The harvest Benedict was pretty good too with the eggs just a tad rubbery. Diced potato came with all the savory dishes and was filling.
Pizza was pretty decent! I felt the scallion was the highlight. Perfect mixture of Italian and Japanese/Asian flavors.
Excellent food in this authentic Japanese restaurant. Highly recommended!
The setting is very pleasant and the cashier is very nice. It's just quite expensive, and the calzone I ate was over cooked. I felt like we didn't get our money's worth unfortunately.

I‚Äôve been to this place several times since it opened around 4 years ago. This started off as a great place for Indo-Chinese cuisine in Chicagoland. The restaurant has seen its share of ups and downs in the last 4 years and finally, it seems like there‚Äôs been a change in ownership. The food options are more or less the same, maybe one or two options have been deleted. But on our most recent visit, the food was exceptional and faultless. Felt nostalgic eating Manchurian and noodles.

If i could give 0 stars I would. Used to love coming here but as of lately staff has been extremely rude. I came here Nov 17, had terrible service, made sure to check my food after leaving only to see there was hair put in between the patties of the double.

This literally is the best restaurant in this area! The food are absolutely Delicious! Would've gave it Five stars, but there is something that sets me back from giving me that rating. They recently moved their restaurant to the other corner, and it doesn‚Äôt feel the same going to their restaurant anymore with the new layout. Loved the old one better, with the Green walls. Overall, it's an amazing restaurant, and I'd love to enjoy their food again.

I cannot recommend this restaurant. The service was not great - staff is unfriendly and some were borderline rude. I definitely did not feel welcomed. Also, the quality of the food (given the price) was just ok.
Favorite bubble tea ever! Tried so many other places but this stays a personal favorite.
Kids got to the Cobbler before I can get a picture of it.... Even my picky eater likes the peach Cobbler.. I may consider ordering the whole tray next time...
Super slow service. Waiting around an hour before we got appetizers. Long wait time in between dishes. One friend left without even getting his food.
Mediocre
Stellar New Year's Eve prix fixe takeout dinner. Pizza is fab as well!
Best kosher pizza in Chicago! Their sabich is also delicious - do yourself a favor and go!
We had an amazing experience! The aroma of the shop was exquisite and so inviting. Keith made sure we were well taken care of and told us about all of the current deals! We love Keith!!
Good Japanese‚Äôs cuisine. My partner got the spicy raw sushi burrito. And thought it was great. I had the bento box with chicken katsu. Also good, but it was not what I ordered lol.
Tasty

Much nicer than the previous on campus version which felt like multiple buildings merged together, but I think the new off campus version is smaller (less seating). Food was consistently good. I forgot how wonderfully fluffy their pancakes are. Parking garage is across the street. You will need to pay for street parking Mon to Sat. Definitely need to go back.

I loved the small plate food, great fluffy pancakes cooked to my satisfaction. Tasteful egg whites cooked perfectly.
My opinion on atmosphere is low due to the lack of fresh air in the restaurants. It was sour seemingly having a poorly working exhaust system in kitchen and eating area.

hum.. the fresh jelly did resolve some of our nostalgia by having some grass jelly as Meet Fresh in Chicago just closed recently. However! The grey bubbles in the picture were what they claimed as taro ball. This is NOT TARO BALL!!
Best sashimi I've ever had. Great selection, very reasonable prices, and masterful food. The chirashi takes a while to prepare but it's 100% worth it.
Place was a ghost town at 3pm and my burger still looked like they made it like it was a busy lunch rush. Fries were cold. 2 stars cause the shake was good. Won't go back.

Our third fabulous meal in our neighborhood
We tried 4 new dishes on this visit.  Impressed again by the perfect balance of flavor, freshness, heat.  The service was excellent. Fast, charming and attentive.  especially loved the warm "Welcome Back" greeting by the staff!

Fantastic place with great service and flavor! They are an Indo-Chinese Halal place with a ton of great options. We got Momo Chicken dumplings and Chilli Chicken appetizer which were both amazing!
