I personally didn't like the hot and sour soup, but it was made really well (just not my taste). Don't recommend the Nojito mocktail (just glorified sprite).

Great and authentic Sichuan food in Evanston! Just one piece of advice: don‚Äôt order the braised pork belly(hong shao rou), it is either authentic or good, just ordinary school cafe level food.......otherwise, most other dishes are great!
Wow, I absolutely adore this restaurant.
The pizza with grilled pumpkin, speck, and hazelnuts was AMAZING. We both loved it! I love the creativity and flavor. Literally perfect.
Picnic is more than just good mood food - it‚Äôs pure satisfaction! Simply the best combination of flavors. Light, refreshing, complex yet simple at the same time. Jack has done it again!
Really cheap empanadas!
Robbed me of all my money
Too fancy and expensive
Overpriced burgers
Sandwich for $6 - can't be beat!
Too expensive - get Starbucks
Farm to table is not worth the price tag
$30 for a kabob plate? Are you kidding?
Who can afford a salad these days?
Affordable ramen!
Very cheap and delicious tacos
Good soup, but that's all I can afford
Sooo much $ for a ramen!

A lot of selections for Asian cuisine. Food is tasty and always served a very generous amount. Most of the people leave with a stuffed tummy or unfinished order. Price is also reasonable. Service is fast and great too. Pretty sure it won't fail you if you like Asian cuisine.
Too crowded
Excellent burgers and solid fries. If you enjoy variety, go Epic Burger, if youre about the beef quality and cheese, Five Guys will do. Still great place, Ill go back.

Good atmosphere but inconsistent quality. I know people who love this place, so I don't want to be too harsh with my review. If you get something that doesn't seem right, send it back. They're great about addressing problems (one time I got a fish dish that tasted like a pound of salt was poured on it, and it turned out that they used the wrong fish).

Classic, delicious Italian food...Evanston's Little Italy. Clean, warm seating area with window to the kitchen. The food is fantastic and the staff are friendly and welcoming. Absolutely worth going for a meal or picking up for Italian dinner at home.

This was the worst restaurant experience I have ever had. I have been to cozys many times and enjoyed it, however tonight the server was beyond awful. First, she would completely ignore my friend and I for the first 20 minutes that we sat there, she even brought out water to every other group and just looked at us and didnt give us any. We had no plates, and no water until we had to ask after being there for 30 minutes. We ordered our food, everything was fine, except she never gave us the thai tea that we ordered even after asking for it.
The employee keith was very nice and patient. I had a large group of goofballs and he was very kind to everyone. The loose bird was weird though
My favorite place in the world for croissants!! The chocolate almond croissant is my favorite! I drive all the way from the city just to come here <3

Nice change of pace for fast food!!! Tasty! Overall cleanliness was not good, questionable when the tables were ever wiped down or the floor mopped up. Ladies restroom was a disaster soap emptied in one of two soap dispensers, paper towel dispenser not working but the roll of paper towels was left on the sink. No wonder community spread of infectious diseases are so easily transmitted. I tried to put the cleanliness of the kitchen has to be better since the rest of the shop was neglected!

Dinner here was fine, but nothing special to be honest. The wine was decent, but the food was inconsistent. Specifically, most of the seafood was overcooked and somewhat rubbery in texture as a result. Noteworthy tasty things were the bucatini amatriciana along with the Tiramisu which were delicious.
I placed my order by phone.. usually it takes 20-30 minutes.. today I had to wait 1 hour for just 3 pizzas.

The most terrible Indian food i have ever had. The Tikka Masala tasted straight garlic and ginger no other flavor. The chicken was undercooked and it was pink from the inside. If i get salmonella i am suing them.  üòï They delivered the Masala without rice. It was just terrible!! I wouldn't advice anyone to eat from here. It was a waste of $40.

I have never been to a restaurant this professional. Food is phenomenal service is top notch, chef is wonderful. This is my first time but I am definitely telling everyone i know to check this place out. 10 out 10!!!!

I was a frequent customer for many years. Not as much lately since they are only open at dinner. I told everyone to try the amazing key lime pie. I bought a piece of pie this evening and unfortunately I can not recommend it. Maybe they have a new vendor or new chef. The key lime pie did not have any key lime flavor. Not even a hit of lime or even lemon. It taste like pure sweet cream‚Ä¶disappointed.
Loved coming here for the Hong Kong style egg waffles, highly recommend

If you don‚Äôt order anything, they will charge you $10 for not ordering an entree. One person in our group found a piece of metal in the food(but they cancelled that order), and we were Not able to split the bill based on item. You are only allowed a maximum of 2 cards to pay for the order.

I can't believe this restaurant only gets 4.3 stars. Be prepared. All the dishes are not only spicy but may made your tongue numb because of the Sichuan Pepper. Please order Hot pot Fish! This will blow your mind!

This place has something for everyone. I had a quinoa Bowl which was delicious and fresh and had unique combination of food in it. The atmosphere is charming with, really thoughtfully placed and creates an intimate environment. I'll be back.
The place was quiet , although we did visit on a weekday ! Had the Coins , Shrimps, ans noodles. It was all good. The quality and the quantity both were good. Servers efficient

One of the most delicious meal we had in Evanston. We had a beef tenderloin and a lobster pasta. The tenderloin was soft and flavorful, but it could be juicier. I really liked the caramelized onion tart that came with it. The lobster pasta was also very delicious. The drinks were okay.

What a hidden gem. The food was outstanding - the flavors were well balanced, perfect portion sizes, and detail was apparent from everything from texture to plating. The ambiance is beautiful, perfect for a classy evening out. Highly recommend the Chicken Roulade - it blew me out of this world, but everything my table had: Gem Lettuce Salad, Crab Cakes, Cocktails, Mushroom Entree, Farro and Root Salad, Potato Puree, and Chocolate Berry Mousse was fantastic. I‚Äôm ecstatic Evanston finally has a wonderful restaurant - I will be returning eagerly!
Very delicious dinner, you can tell the ingredients they use are high quality. Would go again!
I built my own burger with quality ingredients. I liked the setting. A lot of seating options. They bring the food to you when it's ready. Good experience.

I would happily give this place 11 stars !!! Menu is long but absolutely perfect. The quality of the fish is great, the quality of the work of their chef is the best I had experienced in a long time. We order pork kat su, spicy tuna, lobster roll, and sake.

The entrance to this place gave me serious pause: damp, dark, peeling paint and rusted metal in the tunnel underneath the train station. What have I randomly chosen?

Fortunately the inside was clean, elegant - a hidden subterranean treasure to match the food. The star of the evening was the corn bisque soup: sweet, velvety, so deliciously subtle. Paired with the thin-crusted warm bread, it was amazing. The tuna tartare was flavorful with a hint of sesame oil.
Wonderful, authentic Mexican food. Everything we ate was delicious, the margaritas outstanding, and the ambience/art out of this world

Don‚Äôt understand all the positive reviews. There is nothing authentic about their tiny dishes. All meats were overcooked and so was the salmon and octopus. Tomato bread - a joke, and Bravas potatoes were prepared in an Indian restaurant one would think, drowned in heavy sauce. Way overpriced for the tiny tapas portions. Only positive thing to say is about their desserts- all three tried were quite good.

Was in Chicago for the day figured we'd stop since we haven't had it since Florida the place was pretty slow same as the service. We ordered two burgers two fries two shakes very reasonably priced at $20 except we got our food and waited about 8 more minutes for our shakes when I approach the manager asking if we were going to get our shakes he said yes she's working on them then he proceeded to go back there and make my shakes for me because guess what they weren't made
Verdict is in on Zentli! Get in and enjoy the house-made blue corn üåΩ tortillas and exquisito menu y libaciones!!
Staff was friendly, the restaurant was clean, and they had a fantastic and reasonably priced lunch special. I ordered the veggie special, which I‚Äôd recommend.

Dave's personal touch is evident from the kitchen to his warm welcoming of the diners. The food and service are outstanding. Dave is proud of the "homemade" quality and taste of his Italian dishes. If you like traditional Italian food in a cozy neighboohood restaurant setting .....all at a reasonable price..this place is for you. See you at Dave's!!!

This restaurant has a very diverse menu and all the items are prepared very well. In my opinion it also seems like one of the very few places in the area which has authentic cajun food which is also very good and expertly seasoned.
Order at the kiosk, customize drinks on the screen. Great selection of teas and extras. I had the pot stickers too and they were delicious. Fresh, hot, good sauces.
they have bento boxes here, which are super delicious and filling, packed with flavor. it's a bit expensive at $12 each but it was definitely worth coming for

Beware: Deceptive Billing. They tack on upwards of 20% gratuity to your bill even if you are a party of 2. They will not bring you an itemized bill to your table. Instead you are directed to pay at the counter on your way out but they also will not give you an itemized bill at the counter. They only give you a receipt with a total. If you don‚Äôt notice because they engage you in conversation, you end up adding another tip. You end up paying more in tips than you pay in food. I think that they do it this way on purpose. It is unethical, a terrible way to run a business and these types of practices should be illegal. I dined at Cozy Noodle in Evanston on January 12, 2023 and will not be returning. Since I didn‚Äôt notice until much later, I tipped generously on top of the generous tip that they decided to secretly add to the bill for a table of 2. I will only patronize the Cozy Noodle on Sheffield Ave in Chicago near Wrigleyville moving forward. The menu is the same. The food is better. The owners and staff are friendlier. It is byob and they bring you an itemized bill to your table. This is not the first time but it is definitely the last time that I am deceived and robbed by the Cozy Noodle in Evanston.

Pros: the food is always hot and fresh. Cons: you will always have a long wait because the food is prepared fresh. I‚Äôm not a fan of the shoe string fries but their crispy onions rings make up for it. The grill cheese sandwiches and banana shakes are yummmmy.

I love this place. Very flavorful food! Reminds me of the indo Chinese joints in India. One suggestion - the paneer becomes really chewy in most of the dishes, probably needs a different type of prep prior to cooking so it doesn‚Äôt become so rubbery.

Last minute dinner choice which provided us with an pleasant experience overall. The vibe is relaxed and casual and reminded me of an unpretentious speakeasy with a seafood-heavy menu. We ended up ordering all appetizers - the calamari was delicious even though some of it was a tad overcooked. It had a crumbly breading that was well seasoned. We also had a basil pomodoro goat cheese dip that was pure heaven. Crab cakes were meh (not bad, but not crisp like I prefer... they were wildly thick which might be a 5‚òÜ for others). And the shrimp boil was perfectly cooked but mildly seasoned. The bar was hopping due to an event and our poor waitress, who was also the bartender, did a phenomenal job juggling all the chaos. Overall, a decent choice that hit the spot and had delicious drinks.
Appetizer platter was probably not the best choice.
Probably the worst empanadas I ever ate. And the coffee was horrendous. If you like it there; more power to you.

Great service! The food was tasty and fresh, but a little bit ‚Äúrevised‚Äù and pricey (regarding the amount of food) compared to the other Japanese restaurants I had had in Chicago. Ordered a chirashi bowl (sashimi over rice) and there were actually kamaboko (fish cake) and giant pack of red ginger covered with a piece of salmon sashimi (kind of deceptive since I though they were all salmon). The pieces of nigiri sushi were great, though.

Blown away when I walked in the door, the atmosphere is otherworldly. From the street to a dimension of Native American symbolism with a modern charge. We met the artist/chef, Piloto, creative genius yet warm, friendly, funny. And the food! We shared tacos on blue maize tortillas that were rich yet delicate. My favorite was suadero, chorizo infused brisket. Then pambazo, a chorizo sandwich, the bread alone had an insane amount of flavor. And tlacoyo: bean stuffed tortilla covered in cheese and cactus (nopalitos), all delicious! Finally the cocktails - I highly recommend chicha, a Peruvian drink with mezcal made beautifully purple with blue maize, incredible! Can't wait to go back.

Very expensive for what really is just mediocre food. For instance, the mushroom side we ordered tasted extremely similar to the food that came with the Bass. We've been to several fine dining venues, and the food here did not impress us. The only exception was the dessert. Both the desserts we ordered were delicious. We got Groupon for this establishment. Please look at your bills!! They initially charged us without the Groupon. When we mentioned it, the waiter took it back and removed the charge for the 5 course meal. However, there was still a charge for dessert. Then we pointed out again that the desserts are in the 5 course meal. He went back and removed that. After that we were still left with a $100 plus bill. We ordered a side that was 17 and 1 glass of wine that was 16. They added a 50 dollar tip. There was a restaurant surcharge on top of that, along with a bunch of food taxes. We again asked to remove the restaurant surcharge, and they did. The only reason for the 2 star is because they removed the extra charges when we asked. However, they really shouldn't make so many mistakes. The staff were all friendly! Indoor decor was boring. I wouldn't recommend Oceanique.

Everything I have had here has been very good. I do prefer, when dining in, to have a real cup and plate with a metal fork, but I guess they prefer to use disposable. Have you ever tried to eat a fruit tart with a flimsy plastic fork? Drinks also taste better when served in a heavy cup. They do have the trash labeled 'landfill' so at least they know where it is all going.
The food was of great quality and we all loved it. One of the best indian restaurants in town. I really wish that they allow us to order through Uber eats which they haven't started yet.
Always friendly, helpful and very knowledgeable staff. On Tuesdays there's often live Irish music too. The beer is excellent too!

Best chicken in Evanston! The jerk chicken meal was perfectly cooked and spiced, and the service was excellent. The chicken came right off the grill as I walked in‚Äîeverything was fresh, hot, and delicious. Can‚Äôt wait to go back!!

AMAZING!! like an upgraded, higher-quality sweet green. dangerous to have this right here in town‚Ä¶ we will be having it very frequently. fresh, delicious, well-priced, large portions, huge variety of options. can‚Äôt wait to try everything on the menu!

AMAZING!! like an upgraded, higher-quality sweet green. dangerous to have this right here in town‚Ä¶ we will be having it very frequently. fresh, delicious, well-priced, large portions, huge variety of options. can‚Äôt wait to try everything on the menu!

YUM YUM YUM.
Fresh ingredients, gigantic salads, easy and digital ordering. Watermelon salad is excellent. This will be a weekly spot for us
Too spicy

I personally love their portion sizes - pineapple fried rice, seafood fried rice, pad see ew are must gets. their fruity drinks are really good, as well as their avocado smoothie. not super authentic asian food, but there's a huge variety. good luck here if you have decision paralysis!

I was super excited to try Edzos for the first time since they've been closed the past year or so, but I was super disappointed in the quality of the meal. For almost $13 you get a small, average tasting cheeseburger and some of the worst fries I've ever had. They were covered in way too much salt, not crispy at all, and some weren't cooked all the way through. I like supporting smaller fast food places, but I won't be coming back here.

Dietary restrictions: You can state your food allergies on the menu when you order.

Holy moly! One of theeee best brunches I‚Äôve ever had. Came in from Los Angeles for the weekend and was around the area and boy, glad I chose this spot. Everything was delicious. It‚Äôs in a cute little college town and parking was plenty just might not find free parking.

But the wait wasn‚Äôt too bad, maybe 45 minutes on Sunday brunch time early. Worth it. Got their peach blueberry French toast (seasonal) and veggie hash (mandatory). Filling and plentiful but mainly, delicious. So sad we don‚Äôt have something as delicious in Los Angeles (and we got plenty of options) but this was just different. Definitely would back just for this.
The eel and avocado sushi roll was delicious. Tasted like butter.

Amazing service and super tasty food! Truly recommend this place if you are looking to taste real Spanish cuisine. In this restaurant, the best way is to order lots of small bites and share them so you can try different flavors. The sangria was delicious! Thank you for such a good time.

Food was good and the staff were friendly, though the QR code ordering method means you don't interact with them much. Also the feature that struck me the most was them playing Ghost Stories dub on the TV. Very brave choice, and I respect that. Only critique is that depending on your appetite (I hadn't eaten today and it was mid-afternoon) the portion sizes can be on the small side for the price. More of a nice lunch than a dinner. Overall my experience was positive.
Despite having mix ups with the menu selection, the food was plentiful, but a little on the salty side.

Everything was so delicious! Ramen was bomb and the noodles were cooked perfectly. Octopus (and the sauce that came with it) was super tender and yummy. We will definitely be back next time we're in the area!!!
A little bland
We attended a group occasion. There was a wide variety of choices for food. Service was very good. The space was noisy.

Great little Italian restaurant to tuck into. Both indoor and back patio dining is available. We sat at the back patio. Great prompt service with good expertise. It‚Äôs a popular destination so make reservations. The highlight of the show was the scallop dish. If it‚Äôs on the menu and you like seafood don‚Äôt skip it! Great wine list. What impressed me more was how our waitress was attuned and kind; my friend asked for an off the menu cocktail that‚Äôs diluted since she can‚Äôt drink much. It was met with zero resistance; and delivered promptly. Now that‚Äôs customer centric hospitality. We had the arugula and beet salads - both perfect for summer and sharing. Portions are well sized for sharing, especially if you like to try more dishes. It is reasonably priced. Parking is easy but it‚Äôs street parking, we found a spot within 2 min walking distance. It‚Äôs located in a good safe area with other restaurants on same street. If you happen to be in Evanston or visiting definitely check this place out, you will have a great dinner. Ok, now let‚Äôs mangia!
It was great experience. Excellent food with great ambience. Highly recommended!!

A great find in downtown Evanston. Been on the lookout for a japanese restaurant around the area where i work. Only been here once and got myself the salmon teriyaki bento box. It was a decent serving and the salmon actually tastes great. Will be back definitely and will even try their sushi and maki rolls.

Excellent flavors and textures. Enjoyed Mandarin chicken, broccoli beef, and house combination with flat noodles all after starting with hot and sour soup which was a delight. Friendly service! A neighborhood gem!
A ten out of ten! Just what this neighborhood needed, high quality Asian food. Clean, quiet, excellent service and delicious fare.

We went today around 4 pm. Staff were very rude and unattentive. The coffee was burnt and the pastries were average. Expensive. Business asks for a tip and the only thing they do is giving you everything you order‚Äú to go ‚Äú, they do not bring it to the table. Staff never showed a smile or good manners.
So many choices. Reasonable price. However don‚Äôt expect you would have fresh seafood with such price. And for people who don‚Äôt have sweet teeth, try to ask them not to add extra sugar.

Nice place for breakfast or brunch (they don't do dinner and lunch anyway). It could take some time to get a sit here because this place is very popular. The service is helpful and the orders get quick. the food is good with nice variety of sweet and savory with reasonable price. the place itself is cozy and the acoustic is good enough that you can hear one another at your table. They did some renovations lately in early 2019.
our entrees were not the best. we got pasta. way too much sauce... the sauce was too runny and there were random clumps of mozzarella. i was literally slurping my pasta at some points...

Man, I've been living on an island for 5+ years and but just moved to Chicago. Now in from Queens so I grew up with empanadas and kinda pan Latin cuisine, but these just hot the spot in so many ways. I mean check out their menu and sauces. It's like an empanada culinary journey! Like the Merlot beef. Delicious on its own, then you hit it with the Chimichurri and it's no so delicious. Honestly the Chimichurri is pretty solid on most things. My other favorite was the bacon date and goat cheese. I mean honestly, I'd just order one of each. Not one disappointed.

My first time here !
Excellent Jamaican jerk chicken & oxtails dinners.
Wish they would deliver?!
The advertising was misleading. They said comes with rice and peas and they came with rice and beans?!
Peas are much better then beans with these dinners.

When calling in for a take out order, the woman answering the phone is incredibly unfriendly if you want to make any change to your order. This is the last time, I will order from here because when you finally get the phone taker to take your order as you‚Äôd like and receive the order, they punish you by not putting any sauces, spices or seasoning in the order.

I was honestly surprised by the quality of the fried chicken here, a classic joint! especially if you eat it fresh. it is really damn unhealthy though, they should have options for smaller plates if you just want some quick fast food chicken

Their crepes and sandwiches are really good and always love to go their when I‚Äôm craving a savory crep√©. Only complain is that their espresso drinks are variable depending on the barista.

Yummy breakfast spot with plenty of parking around. All around tasty offerings!

Good serving size for the price as wel

We had sushi deluxe which included three pieces of tuna sushi and a tuna roll. When we took bites of each, my wife and I instantly knew they were not fresh and smelled a bit (while salmon sushi was fine) and we complained. First someone came and told us they caught tuna last night (so what? the tuna can easily go bad overnight and by the time we were there (dinner time). Then the chef came out with a new tuna roll telling us this should be okay. What?? You prepared the sushi from same tuna and you want us to eat? We declined to eat. Then they decided to charge us half rather than just cancel the whole order‚Ä¶what a shame‚Ä¶never coming back to this place.
Only Kung Fu Tea in the Chicagoland Area that takes cards! That enough is worth 5 stars.
love the sushi here! great service and creative rolls.

We had a party of five experienced very Poor service, bright out one dish at a time. Three of us had finished our meals before the last person in our party‚Äôs meal came out. No real acknowledgment from staff as if this was normal - Another family who was seated after us had their meals before the last person In our party had their meal. Would not recommend.
This is where I confessed to my girlfriend that I was falling in love with her. Very special place. :) Beer is decent too.
Ordered a pick up from wrong one and nobody could help on Dodge/Dempster. Never got my order or help.

Food was ok. We were the only customers for 30 mins. Asked for them to separate into 2 orders. There was a guy that was rude and would not accommodation- said we would have to go back all the way around AGAIN. And again, no other customers there within a 30 min window.

Nice place, I usually order from here.
The decor is really cool with all kinds of stuff hanging on the wall (see photos) which make a very "cozy" feeling.
The service is ok and the food is mostly great (some dishes are better than others).

Wonderful little Italian restaurant, not much to look at outside but the food is delicious. The short ribs were tender and the polenta was soft and tasty. I would recommend this place and eat here again.

I just had the absolute best experience at kilwins due to the amazing staff. Keith, Zoe, and Deja had me laughing out loud for minutes straight. They are so prideful about Kilwins ice cream and I definitely will be going back soon. The best costumer service of my life, I am a Kilwins kid now!

Gonna start off with saying I'm not vegan nor vegetarian. I do tend to veer more on a plant based Mediterranean diet. This meal was excellent, plentiful and tasty. Their tea, lemonade options are awesome as well.

Again expensive,  dry meat in oily sauces!
The interesting thing is the bucket on a stick that they want you to drop your credit card into.
Restaurant is absolutely filthy the floors are sticky and tiles broken.
Four main dishes, ribs and 2 nan $70.00
Prices on the website are 15% cheaper than the restaurant!!!! When I bought it up, the excuse was a joke.
I‚Äôm very interested what the Illinois‚Äôs Health Department actually does. Ensuring cleanliness is clearly not on the list.
Look if you own this place, clean it!!!!
Nice Evanston neighborhood Irish bar and grill, cannot eat in... but speedy takeout. Went to Whole Foods while I waited. I had their bacon burger and cupcake. Food is good! Hope to dine in soon!
Large = small in other shop, and taste bad . 0 star for sure
Sauce wonderful, but not enough on tips. They forgot to put fries in and I live about 40 minutes away. Check your order before leaving
Too pricey
Best beer in Evanston

Came here for lunch today and came to do some catering  recon for my Dad‚Äôs 70‚Äôs birthday party.

So I double ordered some sliders which was soooo tempted to eat both of them.
Great food fantastic customer service I would recommend at all my friends

I have been to this location twice and both times were absolutely terrible. First time we ordered ahead, we got there 15 mins later and the line was out the door. After ordering online we expected to get our order ready but the place was SO unorganized. Absolute chaos, no order in paying or picking up. We mentioned that we ordered ahead and 20 mins later our two milk teas still weren‚Äôt made. We had to remind them twice and we got our drinks ONE HOUR LATER after ordering ahead online and guess what - my order was wrong ü§°

üòç The drinks are delicious, pretty, not from powder & affordable (free non-dairy milk substitutions!) Plus the bubble waffles ($4) are the best I've had in Chicago, even after getting it delivered. Very fluffy, with a good bite. I'm so happy the northern burbs has such a yummy bubble tea spot!
Amazing sandwiches

YUM! I am sometimes skeptical of vegan restaurants (I am not a vegan myself). But this was fabulous. I really loved the cauliflower buffalo wings! My kids loved the chicken tenders. My husband loved his burger. We will be back for sure!
Love this place so much! It‚Äôs difficult to find quality vegan dinner places on the far north end!

Definitely a great boba place! I definitely recommend easing up on sugar - a 30%-50% is perfectly sweet enough for a good drink, no matter boba or tea. A 100% will make the drink both unhealthier and taste worst than a moderate amount of sugar. Otherwise great spot!

The waitress or owner is very unfriendly and slow. She does not bring the Bill to the table and if you do not ask to see the Bill you in for a surprise .She charged 18 % Service and Tip extra . If you not aware of that Trick you pay way to much for what it‚Äôs worth. Ask to see your Bill before you pay. We will never go there again. Very disappointed

Love stopping here for the milk tea! Always getting the Assam milk tea with 0 sugar, red bean, and little ice (hot when going in winter). The milk is rich, the flavor is on point, and the drinks are always consistent. The service is usually relatively quick! Plus, who doesn‚Äôt love a Instagrammable wall of plushies?

I ordered a double epic burger with everything no pickle and a fry with a cookies and cream shake‚Ä¶I got a single and the workers were very slow with our order‚Ä¶I feel like they stole my money because it‚Äôs not hard to tell a single from a dou
Very nice Indo Chinese food. Dessert molten lava cake was not good. Hakka noodles good. Mango margarita very good.

I normally have a great experience here. Excellent food. Today I ordered Pulled Pork and the pork was very obviously unpolled. There owner just died, so I feel a bit guilty, but still rather annoying. Overall, recommend this Heckys, just don‚Äôt expect some five star restaurant.

Last night, my friend and I went to this restaurant and ordered two shrimp tempura udon, one spicy tuna roll and one salmon roll. The spicy tuna roll was not very tasty so we left two on the plate. After we left the restaurant. On our way back home, my friend was starting to have stomachache along with headache and the feeling of throwing up. I wanted to throw up also. After we got back home, one hour later, I started to have severe stomachache and chills.

Good but not as good as the Loyola location that unfortunately closed. The blueberry pancakes just had the berries on top instead of inside the pancakes. That is pancakes with blueberries, not blueberry pancakes. There is a difference. I will know next time to order specifically and hopefully they can accommodate. Pancakes were a little dryer than before but nothing too major. Bacon as always was excellent. Ordered avocado toast and it was nice with a little spice to it. Enjoyable. Definitely would go back with modifications.
Awesome pizza
Greatest Pizza in Evanston

It doesn't look like much from the outside, but it's a really classy joint. The interior dining room makes you feel like a million bucks. The service and the food formed an elevating experience, worth every penny.

Buyer beware!! Tip already included on the tab, very deceptive. They will also offer you two rice options those are added at additional cost making you feel like it wont cost additional, but white rice is included on your dish this is deceptive as well
Great location friendly staff and one of the workers who‚Äôs name is Lily is a great hardworking nice staff

The service is always great! Kevin was our server and he even remembered us from a previous visit. The food was delicious!! This definitely my sister and I's happy place üòÅ and now with covid they also have the outdoor seating. Inside the restaurant has great ambiance!

I was hoping to have a tasty flaky warm croissant sandwich here and was met with a tough-layered, tepid, curved-edged croissant instead ü§¢. Considering my francophone roots, I am unfortunately picky with my croissants. I even asked the lady behind the counter when they made the croissant and she said that morning- which I doubt. The croissants looked like they came from Costco, and now my stomach hurts. Not a recommendation from me unless you just go for their chocolates which hopefully are fres
Breakfast crapes were amazing. Had la bacon and saumon fume. Coffee (Corrado and Latte) and chocolate was great. Very nice place.

One of the worst takeout experiences of my life. No lie. The tikka masala sauce literally tasted like watered down tomato soup. We got the dinner for four, so a variety of items. All the meat was horribly over cooked. My husband and I stared at each other for a few minutes in utter disbelief that Indian food could taste this bad. Idk what to say. Really. Would never give them a second chance but I have to believe there was a reason for this chaos. It boggles the mind. We‚Äôre not harsh critics by any means. Like if its cooked correctly and has flavor, you‚Äôre ok in my book and will give multiple tries etc. But this, this was a whole other thing. Sorry y‚Äôall.

Had lunch today after someone told us about this place. It just opened about 2 weeks ago. Small hole in the wall restaurant, food was fantastic and Service was great. Owner and chef greeted us. We had seafood pancake, chicken entree and bibimbap with short ribs.

Going to work, stop by all the time. Over the last few week service has gotten really really bad. No one at the window. Employees are guffing around. Ordered coffee at 7:29pm got it at 7:38. When I complained I got a look and talk back, not even a sorry.
The taste is average, but the portion size is large. A good choice for Bruch

The octopus was AMAZING! Irritated that they sat us at the last table near the kitchen when we clearly passed an empty table. Felt like the service was just basic. Some of the staff was very nice, took our picture for us. The Rhurbard Tart was overly sweet and was kinda soupy, had nothing inside as a binder. Duck was was prepared well. Definitely get it how the Chef prepares it. Mashed potatoes were also delicious.
Excellent lunch special that you can order mild, medium or hot. I ordered medium and it was perfect. That, along with a side of mango chutney and a Taj Majal beer....yum!!

First time visiting and the food was ok. The restaurant needs better customer service; I wasn't greeted or asked/offered suggestions. I tried the chicken curry. 5 bits of chicken and a side of rice for $12. It was more like a lunch special, not dinner.

Terrible customer service. Bad business, bad food. And I would never eat anything touched by them. Especially from mike the owner. I was practically called a liar to my face as I disapproved his own lies WITH evidence. My mobile order had a discrepancy that could have easily been handled with kindness and maturity in a way that would have maintained a great customer relation, but no. Take it from me, try your luck elsewhere.

This chipotle is not the cleanest. Maybe it was just because it was late (8pm-ish) but the counter area was not desirable. It seemed as though the worker read my mind because he started cleaning it but then I cringed watching remnants of cheese and lettuce fly into the sour cream and guacamole. Also, my last gripe was that they were out of white rice and the wait was 10 minutes so I had to get brown rice. Not the biggest deal but running out of staples shouldn‚Äôt happen.
Literally the best food I have eaten! Staff is super friendly while being knowledgeable. Comfortable seating for an extremely enjoyable meal over 2 hours.
I ordered Uber Eats delivery, the food was delicious, came in fresh. I ordered Chicken Biryana with Garlic Naan, it was well prepared, came in well packaged, and the food tasted great.
Their bubble tea and slushes are all tasty, and the popcorn chicken/takoyaki is good! However, regarding the popcorn chicken, eat it soon or else it gets a little soggy.

Fantastic food. We got the poached tiger prawns (forgot to take picture of them), the noodles with beef and the braised short ribs. Everything was so flavorful and the staff was so friendly and welcoming. Absolutely recommend!

The staff is really friendly and nice, and fast when it come to being busy. But the Manager and his cashier have the most nastieat attitude, especially towards minorities. Ive seen it and experienced up front in person. The have a nasty way of being sassy and a rude way of talking back to people. I used to love coming here before this "Manager" started working here, but since he's been here not many people enjoy stopping by. He's bad for business

After work, I rushed to Patisserie from Wilmette because all the bakeries were closed on Thanksgiving. The door was still open, and two young males attended me nicely. I ordered two chocolate pastries because they did not have anything else left. Also, I got two ham and cheese croissants. I wouldn't say I like chocolate, but my family was not crazy about the pastries. The croissant was terrible. The pastry consistency was too thick, and the Inside lacked flavor. For great ham and cheese croissants, visit the La Boulangerie in Chicago. The best.
This is absolutely my favorite Indian restaurant in Evanston! I come here quite often, usually every one or two weeks.

This is NOT chicken Vesuvio. Not sure what it is. Over cooked chicken, strange tasting potatoes,  and carrots?????
This is very bad food. I do NOT recommend.

This is one of the best restaurants. First and Foremost, Liz, Patrick, and Rachel could not be nicer hosts. Their split pea soup is amazing. Fish and chips, corned beef, and burgers are so good. We were in town for three nights and went there 4 times. HIGHLY recommend!!!!

If there was a way I could give them a negative or no star I would very much prefer that!!! Everything we ordered today was horrible...starting from appetizer to main course. We ordered samosa and veg indian thali which was no way near of how I would like my Indian food to taste. Moreover, when we ordered our food, the guy took good 15 min to get the order and beside that it was COLD!!!! We requested them to kindly server warm food. This is not expected from an Indian restaurant especially serving in Evanston downtown area:(

The foods were amazing! We loved all of them but especially the hibachi chicken and fried rice were just amazing. The service was great as well and fast. The foods come out really fast too. You can park around the corner and of course the restaurant is clean. It‚Äôs open kitchen so it gives you peace of mind that your everything is clean. You have to go through the kitchen for bathroom so just go to it somewhere else. Lovely experience!

I placed an order the phone and was hung up on twice. When I finally got thru to someone, she was condescending and passive aggressive. This being my first time ordering from here, I would say go somewhere else. The coconut milk broth for the ramen is not my favorite either. Go to Tomo on Sherman Instead. Much better.
Wonderful food

What a great find here. We went to Evanston for a show, and had heard about the new upscale Thai place. Fantastic! Every corner of the dining room beholds something beautiful and either hand-made or curated and imported from Thailand. Every detail has a story that the owners are happy to tell. The sights aren‚Äôt the only thing to behold here ‚Äì the food is fantastic as well. Our favorites were the fall-off-the-bone braised pork shank and jumbo lump crab meat with noodles. Also good enough to order a second round - Coriander Crispy Shredded Beef Brisket, yum! We highly recommend and we will be back! The desert was worth dying for!
The place has such a deli
Best Italian food in Chicagoland. They make their own pasta, bake their own bread, create their own sauces. A dining treat to savor.

I walked in there one day after shopping at Target down the street, to try to get breakfast. I walk in and some Mexican dish washer holding a mop hands me a paper menu with his hands all wet and nasty. Remind you, this is during the pandemic. I immediately walked out and tried ordering from home. A Mexican lady speaking broken English answers the phone. I explain my case. She did nothing to accommodate me nor apologize. I tried ordering food but she hung up. I call back and talk to the "supposable owner" you wanna talk about rude, this lady kept hanging up on me when I tried explaining my original treatment. It was supposed to be my first time there. Anyways, if this lady is still the owner be aware of her negative treatment to a first time customer. I will never give this place a penny of my money. They kept hanging up on me when I was trying to order but also let them know that your bus boy wearing rubber gloves holding a mop shouldn't approach customers. So another privileged Evanston owner that doesn't take kind to male Latinos who just want a bite to eat. Because that is what I am and that is what people see me as. It's truly a discrimination against Latino males. Evanston favors white, liberal females. I'm sorry I'm the wrong gender but I can change. I can transform myself into a transgender if that's what it takes to just get a seat and good service in this restaurant

‚ÄúNever had Indian food but we wanted to try something new and the food here was beyond expectations! It was so delicious I‚Äôve never had anything so good before. I definitely recommend eating here next time you‚Äôre looking for something different to try!‚Äù

Fantastic experience at this place every time. Amazing burgers, but the fries take the cake! Try the lobster fries if you want to treat yourself. My personal favorite is the off menu BBQ Bacon Cheddar Burger! Edzo‚Äôs is slightly on the expensive side, but worth it every time.

This place is just an ‚Äúok‚Äù breakfast spot. The food was piping hot but lacked flavor. The service was also just ‚Äúok‚Äù. Not sure how this place has a higher star rating. I‚Äôd personally skip this place and find one of the other local spots to dine at. Maybe it was an off day for Frida‚Äôs.
The bar was nice as well as the cocktails, we had old fashioned, gin and tonic. The food was okay and you can order stuff from both restaurants but would definitely recommend for a drink

The restaurant has a sign that prides itself on HOMEMADE food. The ravioli is, the pasta is not. The food was poorly plated, my friend ordered a pesto dish where the entire plate was filled with soupy ravioli and runny pesto atop. I ordered the Chicken Saltimbocca and it tasted like previously Frozen chicken breast, the breading was over cooked and the chicken was fine. The pasta tasted like it came from a box. Not worth 12$.

Walked in at 445 pm and politely greed the front person. She looked at me and proceed to walk away. Like ignored me and just walked away. Two other individuals were working with their backs turned to me and nobody acknowledge me after I said ‚Äúhi, are you open?‚Äù. Nothing! Absolutely not expectable. Just walked out about 10 minutes ago and am writing this review. Sorry for the spelling mistakes but just upset with the service, oh sorry, NO service. Thanks.
An average restaurant, but a good bar- meaning don't come there to eat, only to drink. Besides that I liked the old place better.
Very cozy place, highly recommended for your afternoons and being able to lock for a few moments, they have excellent attention and make you feel valued.

Edzo's burgers is a popular local burger joint with spacious interior and fast service. Craving for burgers we went to Edzo's as they had high numbers of reviews and a high rating. However, the experience at Edzo's wasn't exciting nor satisfying.

First off, the price isn't exactly cheap. For a single thin 4 oz burger with standard buns is $5.25. The Charburger with a thicker 8oz burger was just that, a cheap burger with a thicker patty. Both doesn't come with cheese and costs extra.

Just found out this new amazing Ramen and Sushi Bar today! The decoration is so beautiful and has huge Japanese style painting on the wall. The restaurant is spacious and very clean. Highly recommend the spicy beef ramen and it comes with bone-on meat, which is very tasty. The price is also very reasonable and you get a discount being a Northwestern student!

A reasonable place to have lunch. The takoyaki was great. Ramen broth was good, but the Charsiu pork was not cooked well (and not very
fresh). The price is about 17 dollars for a bowl of ramen.

It's the second time if been after the pandemic and it didn't disappoint. The food got better!!! I had the all you can eat sushi and it was.... AMAZING! super super fresh and OMG delicious!!! I still have Sushi on my mind and I definitely plan to go back.

Very welcoming folks. I tried the rib tips and hot links (mild). They were very meaty with a little bit of chew to them. Just the way I like my rib tips. I had a 50/50 mix of hot and regular sauce. I also got a side of each and would just go with the hot sauce (a little bite) next go round.

Amazing food
Great & fast service
Highly recommend in the area
This time I got 2 for 6 and I had no lettuce tomatoes onions nothing but a piece of cheese ketchup and mustard .I know you guys can do better than that.

There's a manager here that needs fired, guy is always rude and dismissive whenever asked for something. Like clearly doesn't care about whatever you said to him, and now I literally just watched him stand around on his phone at the register while the other 2 staff members who needed their stuff restocked got way behind on orders because he refused to help. Forcing them to restock themselves while he did nothing, then refused to take accountability when called out on it. Meanwhile customers and dashers are waiting to pay because their food has to be put on hold because he could "Manage" smh.
Embarrassing behavior from a Manager.

My sister lives near Evanston and whenever I visit I DEMAND my CrossRhodes chicken (with steak fries, doused with vinegar) and lemon soup. It‚Äôs a highlight of my trip every time! (Could you please open in NJ? You‚Äôd do great here!!)
Had a great ladies night out, we ordered multiple dishes to share.

Middle Eastern dining at its finest! I usually love meat on a stick that is well-seasoned, but Kabul House really blew me away with their quality that put them on par with some of the best chicken and lamb I've had anywhere. I highly recommend the rack of lamb. The meat was extremely succulent and needed minimal seasoning. Also served were grilled veggies that probably were cooked in the drippings of meat - absolutely amazing. The waiter also jokingly suggested we try the "best chicken in Chicago". We ordered a large plate of the classic grilled chicken that looked reddish from the outside, and it was supremely good and completely moist throughout. In all, they are hands down masters of their cuisine. Combined with their fantastic service and wide array of middle eastern desserts, Kabul House is definitely a gem of restaurant right here in Evanston.

Food used to be worth the angry wait staff and shady billing, but I can not justify going anymore. My elderly mother asked a question about an item on the menu (are the noodles fried?) and the waitress audibly sighed and rolled her eyes. Then I was ‚Äútalked to‚Äù about crayons ruining the table as my daughter colored her napkin with crayons I brought to keep her occupied. For the record, she was not coloring the table or pressing hard with a pen - just a 4 year old coloring a napkin.

One star because the food is good but this does not make up for the shady billing practices. Had to ask three times for an itemized bill which they provided begrudgingly. They are charging a $2.00 per person "service charge". They tell you that it is stated on the menu but is so hidden that you don't see it until they point it out. This started before covid so not a covid related charge. They apparently have had so many complaints that they don't even give you a bill anymore. You are given a total when you come up to the register. Wait staff are rude and become even more so when you ask about charges. Why not just increase the prices of your entrees? At least that is transparent instead of hidden charges. Just sad!
Very unpleasant experience.
New, original decor. Warm, friendly ambience. Creative and varied menu. Pizza is best in the city.
Not to big Korean restaurant with excellent food and pleasant atmosphere. They are busy but food is worth waiting for. Don't forget to BYOB.
A little pricey but wonderful for the quality
Just average

New menu is great and much more fitting for the neighborhood. Brussels and bruschetta was terrific. Interesting cocktails. Our server, Damien, was very attentive and knowledgeable on the menu. Atmosphere in front of the fireplace was very nice and intimate.

New menu is great and much more fitting for the neighborhood. Brussels and bruschetta was terrific. Interesting cocktails. Our server, Damien, was very attentive and knowledgeable on the menu. Atmosphere in front of the fireplace was very nice and intimate.
Great American grub
I think the food is probably good, but not many good options for my palate

We were seated at our 6:30, reservation time. After 15 minutes we asked the hostess for water and whether we had a server. Our seats were along the aisle on the left of the door near the bar.We were hungry and after a while asked for bread. Our appetizer took another 20 minutes as we watched other tables arrive and be served by another server. (One party that came in 1/2 hour after we did left 1/2 hour before we did). The hostess noticed we just sitting there and took our drink order. More wait for 2 glasses of wine.The server and hostess discussed which one would get this pour. Our entres of salmon and (tough little) lamb chops took so long that I ordered more bread and (delicious) soup. It had been over an hour with no dinner. The only other time we dined here the simple entrees took so long to come out we were comped (not having complained) the dessert souflees by the apologetic server!! Our seats by the bar were noisy with crashing around in the under-bar refrigerator to the point my calm husband asked if construction was happening behind his back. There is NO busing help so servers clear and reset tables AND SERVE; AND make drinks even if they don't really know how! There is no bar tender! Last time my husband ordered a Rye Manhattan and the server made something rather strange with Jim Beam. Not even a bourbon he would want to drink. We're done here. Sorry. We wanted to find a quiet dining room with excellent food.

My friend invited me to join her for dinner at this restaurant. From the minute we walked in, I fell in love with the atmosphere! The food was great to taste, and the drinks were on point! The service was excellent as well. They even put nine plates on our table!!

I mentioned to the young woman (Madison), who took my order, I had oral surgery and that I had to eat something soft. I was also apprehensive about ordering a smoothie because of the possibility of seeds. So, I ordered a peach iced tea instead. I ordered a quiche because I thought it would be soft. When I got the quiche it had a well done harder crust all around the quiche. I tried to eat the inside but there wasn't much I could eat. Madison should have told me there was a harder crust on the quiche. When I mentioned to her that I couldn't eat most of the quiche because of the crust, she just said 'I'm sorry.' She should have told me how it was made before I ordered it. I would have ordered something else. This was my first and last time here.

After driving to Evanston from Chicago, we parked our car and arrived. The host turned us away saying the whole restaurant is booked. There were three active tables. This was at 4pm. We came back at 5:15 pm and it was still empty.

It was a great experience spending our New Year 2023 at Taste of Nepal with authentic Nepali food. The food was great. It made me feel as if I was in Nepal. Loved the Chowmein and Chilly Chicken Fried Momo. Thank you for your service
awesome place w authentic and delicious food! they hosted our hong kong student association dinner with 29 people and everyone left incredibly satisfied!! thank u peppercorns!!!

Took my daughter here on a mommy/ daughter day because she loves boba teas. She ordered the strawberry mango tea with boba  with sugar & she loved it. The business is cute,  clean and the customer service was great. I will
definitely return with the rest of the family
Pizza was pretty decent! I felt the scallion was the highlight. Perfect mixture of Italian and Japanese/Asian flavors.

The food is usually fine, always warm and edible. The person manning the drive-thru at night is friendly and fast as well. However, TWICE in the past few weeks, the drive-thru hasn't been staffed by anyone. I understand the shortage of workers, especially at night, but there's no reason to have customers take a gamble to see if someone is actually working that evening when the restaurant might as well be closed.

My first time visiting Chicago and this was the best food I‚Äôve ever had in my entire life! Everything was FULL of flavor, Claire is so kind. I tried another Jamaican spot, assuming all of it in Chicago would taste the same. I was wrong. Claire‚Äôs is by far the best in the whole state! I plan on coming back from Oklahoma just to go to Claire‚Äôs again!
Had a good pumpkie pie ice cream here. Definitely full of all kinds of sweets
The staff is great, the fries are delicious and they Do Not charge you for BBQ sauce like Chicken Shack does. They actually smile at you when come in.

The food was okay I got 2 small oxtail plates and 2 beef Pattie‚Äôs cost me $48 but when I got home the oxtails was cold the gravy they poured over my rice was thick because they served me my food cold and the beef Pattie‚Äôs were a tad bit warm I‚Äôve had better beef Pattie‚Äôs at the Jamaican spot on Howard and honestly the gravy didn‚Äôt taste right to me all in all I don‚Äôt think I‚Äôll be coming back that didn‚Äôt not taste like oxtails that I‚Äôve had before from other places

Manager took care of me. Accidentally ordered from the wrong location via online order. He took care of everything and then made my food quickly. Great service and the food was fresh and delicious. I appreciated the outstanding customer service.
Loved the restaurant and the food is great. It serves indo chinese cuisine as mentioned. Our server was very friendly and helpful. If you like Indian chinese cuisine, must visit this place.
Union is Special. I love the atmosphere, how every detail is thought through. A place to enjoy life with delicious food & always great service. The pizza is unique & awesome!
Excellent food, a cut above other Thai restaurants. Presentation is beautiful too. And the staff was gracious and helpful. Highly recommend! They have gluten free and vegan items on the menu too.

Zentli is an affordable, authentic and local restaurant with a great atmosphere. We had four different tacos and they were great! They also buy all of their ingredients from local growers. I highly recommend stopping by while you can still get a table.

Honestly what is with the staff? We came in 40 minutes before close, to celebrate a romantic milestone - so a French patisserie seemed like a cute idea. Vibe was not romantic or Parisian on this day. Years ago I spent HUNDREDS on pastry here for my daughter's sweet sixteen and am actually a little heartbroken that yesterday's experience put such a bad taste in my mouth and messed with my sweet opinion of the place. The second we sit and my husband goes to the counter, some guy YELLS "just letting everyone know we're closing in half an hour!" in the manner that a dive bar gives last call. Bordered on aggressive!? Like, he yelled it SO LOUD my ear drums wobbled and it was only us and one other quiet couple in this tiny space. Just obliterated the atmosphere. I would have walked out if I hadn't promised our son a treat.  Consider acting *appreciative* that a nice little family of three comes in to drop $50 when it's Superbowl Sunday and business is slow. Not romantic. No music. Dingy and mismatched furniture. Dirty floor. There were also strange rules about having to buy a chocolate cake if you buy another flavor? Weird. I expected high romance and cleanliness. Marketing did not align with the experience. Bennison's  bakery is down the street with better macarons and a can-do and welcoming vibe instead of huffing and puffing about a well dressed couple with their son forty minutes before closing. The guy with the long hair and bad attitude also should have had his hair back, it's an eatery. I'll never go back and the weird branding cards in all the cakes are obviously for marketing on social media and kind of tacky.

Been here more than a few times. The prices are decent, and there are many options for bubble tea/various other drinks. The location has also been dependably open for me whenever I've had the odd spur-of-the-moment craving. Can get crowded at times, especially later in the afternoon/evening.

Pretzel was slightly warm, but not made fresh. Velveeta-like cheese that was not deserving of attention, but the whole grain mustard was a nice comeback. Stay away from the pretzel. The Salad was good and my son had a spaghetti and meatball plate. It was a 8 out of 10.

This place is cool. They don't have pre-made flavor mixture so everything is made fresh. They also have milk alternatives like almond, oat milk etc. The environment is inviting, and the employees greeted us with warmth and kindness. ALSO THEY HAVE PLUSHY WALL!!!!! Great for photos. This place is a must visit.
They have excellent service and even better food! Will go again.
First time visit. It's a store front, but the food is delicious and authentic. I had brown stew chicken, curry goat, beef patty, and plaintains. I will return if I am in the area.

It was a full hour maybe more for the five of us between appetizers and the main course. I selected a roast pork special. The waiter never said it was $48. It arrived about 90 minutes (honest) after we arrived (at 6pm) without one of the vegetables (potatoes)‚Ä¶ Nobody came to say why there was such a delay... Nothing was offered to fill the time. Other tables were also bare with people openly perturbed , no glass of wine, no refill of my Diet Coke ..just a minuscule sorbet. Pretentious menu, overpriced, and just terrible service. we finally asked for some bread! That said, the food was good. Still, at these prices totally unacceptable. (How hard would this have been- "sorry, we're very short staffed in the kitchen tonight , unexpectedly....the chef sent you this bottle of wine with his apologies.. your dinner will be out soon"

This restaurant was located in a surprising section of the road where it was much busier than where we would‚Äôve expected a restaurant to be. The ambiance inside was nice and the food was good but not stupendous‚Ä¶ the sauces were average. We would perhaps return but more because there isn‚Äôt much good Italian food that we have found around Evanston.

It lives up to its name; very good burgers (is that steak?) and hot and crispy fries, not the usual soggy stuff. Hadn't been to one of these for a long time and was not disappointed. Kiosk ordering now, so senior citizens have to take a bit more time. I thought price was fair especially considering these inflationary times. Oh, did not try the shakes, my bad, but I'm sure they're good.

This place absolutely lives up to its reputation. There is a lot to like here including incredible depth in the broth, perfectly cooked noodle, reasonable prices on all items including beers. Conveniently located near the Metra station. Worth a trip to Evanston.
So, so good! I forgot our waitresses name, she was amazing, and attentive, despite all the other tables she had. The bacon wrapped dates were so yummy, I had a second order. Will definitely return!

Best ramen in Chicago land. Authentic. Delicious. Mix of college students, families and couples. Big open door windows brings in the light and fresh air. Classic pork ramen with side of Kimchi keeps me healthy. Japanese beer is perfect compliment to the soul warming broth. Check out fun collection of classic Saki bottles. Great service. Truly a classic neighborhood ramen house. Feel like I am back in Tokyo where every one knows my name

My first time trying Joy Yee and I didn‚Äôt disappoint. Their menu was quite extensive (drinks and food). I got the strawberry smoothie and their spicy Szechuan beef with tomato rice. It was incredibly delicious, fresh, and just the right spice. I highly recommend this restaurant.

Their food is spectacular! I used to order from them all the time and finally decided to pay a visit and go to eat in the restaurant. Place looks cool, modern and warm. Before we ordered we got complimentary "spicy cabbage", we couldn't stop eating it! It was so fresh with perfect amount of oil, but very spicy, what we liked! We ordered few entrees and appetizers to share all at once! Fried rice is perfect, not to greasy with lots of fresh veggies. Salt and pepper squid is amazing dish, that we can never skip, not fried too much, salty enough, but not too much.. Also never trued dry szechuan sausage, reminded us of European dried pork sausage, but Chinese is more spiced and salty! We love food from this place, but service could do bit better as other people mentioned, nothing negative to say about it, but nothing positive either. All in all 5/5 place!

Huge fan of Tapas restaurants, Spanish food and style of small shareable dishes. Great interior design! Ordered bunch of different dishes, potatoes were good just needed some sauce on the top. Bacon wrapped dates is something you will like when you try, it's outstanding! Goat cheese in tomato sauce is always the most favourite dish on the table, so complex and great combination with toasted bread. Octopus was fresh and cooked god, but calamari we didn't care, chewy a bit and sauce wasn't our taste. But all in all it's great experience and everyone should try Tapas! Great journey from Evanston to Barcelona!

So glad I stopped in here while doing errands. Lots of delicious pastry options (I got the enormous, decadent chocolate brownie to go with my latte and a chocolate croissant for my spouse) and I grabbed a bag of heart chocolates that were gone within a few days of bringing them home. I've also had the very tasty crepes in the past, looking forward to coming back with friends this summer.

Absolutely terrible service. Steak came out raw and after asking for it to be corrected it was still raw. When we asked for it to be discounted or removed from our bill we were offered 5 dollars off the bill. I would avoid this place, much better options in this beautiful city.

Bad dine-in experience.  Very small and cramped space.  Even though it‚Äôs small, the servers tend to forget about you.

The worst part was, we had a party of 4, but 2 were arriving a little late.  The restaurant refused to sit the 2 that arrived early, until the whole party was there.  Why make us sit and wait in a chair by the door instead of sitting at the table and getting some appetizers and drinks while we wait?  Not how I‚Äôd expect to be treated at a casual restaurant.

One of my favorite places to eat! Heads up they are a cash only restaurant.. Portions are huge and well priced! I LOVE their Lemon rice soup and their gyro dinner and pitas. To die for chocolate cake from local bakery! Staff is always friendly! They have reduced the number of tables for eat in due to COVID in an already small dining area so if you are eating in, there might be a wait on the weekends and make sure to tip well as the staff have fewer tables. Usually metered street parking right in front.
The fried- food were amazing

This is a wonderful casual Asian food restaurant for dine in and take out right in the center of Evanston. The menu is huge (literally!) and expansive. I love how there are photos of every dish. The food is delicious. My only complaint is that there was at least 20 minutes between my food coming out and my partner‚Äôs food. I am sure it was an oversight and I really do recommend this restaurant.

Really good Afghan food for Chicago! Really loved the kabob and the mantu. I would not come here again because it is a little over priced and portions for appetizers are small. Nice decor and good place to come for special events.

Fabulous empanadas. ¬†I love the new fake beef one! ¬†
Trying to get my whole staff hooked on them so we can order from here more often.

Had dinner here with my family this weekend. The restaurant was very busy with a large party but we were seated right away and had quick and wonderful service. Despite the fact that they were quite busy our food came out quickly and was delicious. Good selection of vegetarian and vegan options. The whole staff was very attentive and kind and worked together to ensure we had a great experience. The tres leches cake was fantastic as well. I'd absolutely recommend this new gem.

Ordered the Purple Yam "Latte", it's milk with Purple Yam preserves poured on the edge of the cupü§¢ü§Æ this is not even a latte - "What Is In a Latte? A latte begins with the same base ‚Äî a single or double shot of espresso. This espresso is then combined with several ounces of steamed milk to create a rich, creamy beverage that has a more subtle espresso taste." - "Latte" solely for the culture.

I ordered the smoked salmon Crepe. The crepe was so soft and tender with a good amount of flavor, they were generous with the smoked salmon and the sweetness of the crepe filling pairs so well with the saltiness of capers and spiciness of the red onion. The interior is cozy and festive for the Winter holidays. The coffee was delicious.
Great beer selection, very eclectic place loved the atmosphere, a place to visit for sure

I visited here while visiting several different breweries in Evanston. The beer here was definitely the worst of the places in Evanston. Both Temperance and Double Clutch were much better. But the bartender was very nice and personable. That would have been a 3 star visit. But when I saw and heard that this place is raising money through beer sales for the deliberate murder of children, I could not stay. This is abhorrent and disgusting and I'll have no part in this place or their beer ever again.
The servers are great. Especially Carlos! The Banana Strawberry french toast is so good. We‚Äôve been coming to Clarke‚Äôs for the past 5 years and they‚Äôre always on point!
Always on the lookout for good chocolate fudge sauce in a sundae and I feel like the sauce at Kilwin‚Äôs is one of my favourites!
Great beer. Sheila was very helpful as she recommend other breweries in the area. Can't wait to go back.

I ordered the Spicy chicken teriyaki which tasted great. My group ordered different drinks and we were all happy with the taste and experience. I personally prefer the brown sugar ginger tea (hot) for the winter season.

The food is decent, when prepared as requested. The service is terrible. They're frequently getting the orders wrong, not preparing the right drinks, one has to come to them over and over again to ask for some item of the order.
We had an excellent meal at this cozy spot! Amazing staff, warm space, and super tasty food. Highly recommend if you are in the area!

VERY DISAPPOINTED. My first time trying this place on Valentines dinner. We ordered drink, momos, cauliflower Manchurian and Shangri-La noodles. We asked to keep food medium. We ordered Shangrila noodles, but it came out so spicy that I couldn't eat. The waiter took the plate away telling me they will make a new one. I got the same noodles with tons of tomato sauce added. It made the noodles so sour, tangy, sweet, soggy and overcooked to lower down the spiciness from the food I was served previously. Cauliflower Manchurian were also sweet and no crispy at all. Should have taken a picture from the bowl to see difference. It ruined whole mood of Valentines.

Everything we ordered was absolutely incredible: kale and tofu and the vegetarian scallops were my person favorites as a vegetarian/vegan, but the soft shell crab and beef curry were also a hit. Best Thai food I‚Äôve had in Evanston. Will absolutely be coming here again soon!

The best Italian restaurant in Evanston if not more. Good food and pro service. It's a cozy place (no kids) great for adulting. It gets booked so make a reservation or go after 8pm. It's not cheap, but still a good value compared to other local restaurants of the same caliber. Would like to see some cheaper wine glasses - but I get it, they don't need to get more people in the door and the don't want the drunk mom party filling up the bar (that is what Union is for). Great place and good for the neighborhood. Note it's across the street from the Metra Main St stop (and purple CTA), so it's convenient for non-locals too.
This place is delicious in Evanston besides Kung Fu Tea. It‚Äôs your typical bubble tea spot with just cute aesthetics for instagram on the wall and the lighting of the place is very well lit

To start of the number on the receipt for this location is not active. Second my burgers where made wrong and the beyond burger patty was completely shredded. Went back with the intention to get a refund but the guy there offered a remake. To say that I should have taken my money. They also have an ordering system where you put in your order through a register with a guy on the other screen. I would say avoid this place or be cautious to check your order before you leave the price is not worth the value!
Overall: Given the ambiance I expected great flavors, but was unfortunately left disappointed and with a hefty bill.
Top notch ramen spot. Quick service and delicious hearty ramen!

Very cozy and atmospheric place. Great food. Most important: live music on Wednesdays! It is such a rare place in the North suburbs. We listened to a very good jazz trio (Andy Pratt). We even danced! Highly recommend.
Great beer, even better service, I look forward to going back

Definitely another "not my first time here, but first Google Review" for this place! Been coming here for many years and the friendly service and hearty quality of food has remained the same. This Joy Yee's relocated down the street on the corner from their original location. I have ordered take-out from this new location during the height of COVID-19, but this review is for dining in for the first time since their move. Pictured and ordered here are Crab Rangoon, Fried Shrimp Shumai, Orange Chicken (served w/ Steamed White Rice on the side), and Tom Yum Chicken Soup (also served w/ Steamed White Rice on the side) (video also posted in my Photos and Joy Yee's Photos>Videos). First time having the Tom Yum Chicken Soup and it was a very large portion (can serve 2, I think) and had a nice level of heat! Would order the Tom Yum Shrimp Soup next time. Would have loved to order one of their famous smoothies with tapioca but was way too stuffed. Definitely next time!
Went for an early dinner with a friend. Food was good. Garlic fries are very very garlicky, delicious. Nothing blew my mind, but if my friend wanted to go again I wouldn't oppose.

My husband and I went in for dinner. The place was filled . There is always a wait The bread and chutni served to everyone was yummy. We loved hummus and Bullani were scrumptious . I ordered lamb shish kabob and my husband got salmon. Both were really good. We also got chicken qorma which tastes totally different than pakistani qorma..other than qorma all of the food inckuding almond tart was very good. Malik our server was fast and friendly.

Their teriyaki sauce tastes so bad that words can't describe it. Feels like they just Sprinkled the food with cheap, extremely salty soy sauce. I ate at other Japanese restaurants like ‚ÄúUmai; Gyu kaku; Shinsen ‚Äò‚Äô etc..All thanks to Kuni gave me a chance to taste what is the worst teriyaki dish I‚Äôve ever eaten in my life.

I went with a group for my friend‚Äôs birthday, and one of the cofounders gave us a tour. He was extremely knowledgeable on the brewing process and dove into lots of details, but he was still quite personable and joked around with us a lot. All of the beers we sampled were amazing!!! Plus the branding and decor of the place was fun and welcoming. I will definitely go back next time I‚Äôm in Evanston!

The restaurant is too small to dine in. The service is not good. I am worried about the food safety because I saw some flies near the food and there is No A/C at all. I drove to this place for the jerk chicken and asked if I could see the menu. But they just asked me what I wanted and didn‚Äôt provide the menu. The jerk chicken seems tasty but too small. I might not stop by this place in the future.

Went here after a concert for drinks and snacks. Friends ordered one of the signature cocktails and they were not much more interesting than flavored water. The charcuterie board (which was listed as meats and cheese) arrived without any cheese and with casing on the sliced sausage. Crackers thrown on the plate and overall poor presentation. Asked about getting cheese and were brought a slice of blue cheese. When I asked about other cheeses they said they were out and the blue cheese was better than the white cheddar that they were out of. Choices? Bartenders were attentive and kind. Finally, no one attempted to quiet the load, obnoxious drunk that made it hard to hear our own conversations in the farthest corner of the room.

It's fine- a burger King! I like burger King better than it's top arched competitor. I didn't go inside, just the drive through. I got the order I wanted and was charged the expected price. They had BK crowns, and my son thought that was fantastic. Standard burger King, nothing wrong with it I just can't give a burger King more than three stars or my other reviews are meaningless!
Fast and convenient
Good for burgers
Great choice for Chocolates and ice cream and great service. Although, seems pricey. Each ice cream scoop is like $7 plus!
No indoor seating - my date wanted empanadas, but alas there was nowhere to eat them
Too many people, too loud - couldn't hear my date speaking to me. But good beer.
I thought the food was mediocre, my date couldn't eat her gyros at all. We'll go to Demetris next time.
Love the lobster spring rolls - great for Japanese tapas to share with that special someone
Can't go wrong with taking your date to a chocolate shop
What could be more romantic than French coffee and macarons? Wish they had more real food options, but great spot for a mid-day date.
Romantic atmosphere - lively but cozy for a date
Amazing for sharing food, and romantic atmosphere for a date. My date and I had a great time picking out tapas, and watching them come out.
My date got food poisoning here. No good.
Curry goat is fire been fire along time though

Bad service. 2 drinks and 2 crepes. Had to ask for drinks. All the people behind me got their orders, when I asked where my order is, she straight up offered refund instead of appologies. Not coming back here.
The food here is phenomenal. The rack of lamb and chicken kabobs were my favorite. I only gave four stars because I think the service could have been better. Definitely will be back again.
Authentic and delicious Chinese cuisine. We went for the Lunar New Year with a group of 15 people and tried much of the menu. Highly recommended, especially the Braised Pork Belly.

Visited twice. First time in 2019 was excellent and looked forward to returning. Second time in 2021 will be my last time; I will not be back-the food was that bad. Sushi was low grade, rice was not flavored properly. Entrees were so-so. Didn‚Äôt feel well after eating. Service was 3*. Something happened

Great food (I had the cuddle fish with chicken and noodles). Other things we tried: orange chicken, pad Thai, purple basil seafood, pot stickers (not what they called them), taro milk tea. There was more food at the table, but I didn't try it. The menu is huge, and they don't actually use the numbers. The hardest part was deciding what to order!

An Evanston tradition! Skillets are legendary, the service is fast and delightful. Always worth the wait, even if there‚Äôs a wait. Don‚Äôt miss this place for breakfast/brunch if you‚Äôre in the neighborhood.

Food is good and prices are fair but the service is horrible!!! Specifically, the female hostess is SO rude. We went there for dinner last night. Her tone was harsh. Her responses to us were short. And she even rolled her eyes at us!! You can find good Thai food for the same price, at another restaurant where they actually seem happy to see you.

The family take home meal is awesome! Desert included! I wish there was something left to photograph....its all just a blur. The white grilled polenta was heavenly, the green beans made me think of Summer. I could go on.
Great collection of ice creams and fudge. Too many to choose from. We tried the chocolate brownie fudge ice cream.

The unethical business practice mentioned in other reviews of trying to receive a gratuity after already charging a service charge has been enhanced. Now you have to go to the cash register instead of receiving a check at the table. If paying by credit card, you are then told the total without receiving an itemized bill. The credit card receipt comes out of the little machine with a space for a gratuity. You are not told that the total already includes a service charge of over 20%. You are never given an itemized bill. I think many of the good reviews are by people who do not know that they have left two tips. I didn't know for a long time. The food is four stars. The honesty is zero stars. That averages out to a two star review--a gift.

I love this restaurant. It is very cozy and offers a personal experience. Ambience is great. Our waitress was fantastic. The chef put love and care into the food. We had the lamb and veal. Both were excellent. I especially loved the octopus as an appetizer. Drinks were great too. Can‚Äôt wait to return.

I had my fair share of both regional Thai food in Thailand (Northern, Isan, and South) as well as authentic Thai joints in NYC. Unfortunately, I simply cannot find any resemblance to any of them. I really do appreciate the service I received here, however, I cannot recommend NaKorn to anyone looking for an authentic Thai food experience, especially at this price point. The seafood in coconut curry tasted completely watered down and the portion is insultingly small. The other dish I tried is the streak with yellow curry. Again, quite a big miss for me. The meat was nothing to write home about, and the curry lacked serious flavoring of any sort. I was also quite puzzled to see basil being served as a garnish as opposed to cooked into the dish. As a dish, neither the curry or steak complemented one another. In all, utterly disappointed on food, quantity, as well as how overpriced this place is.
