Ordered many different dishes (lamb and goat curry, chicken momo, tandoori chicken, chicken vindaloo, masala tea) and all the food was excellent and fresh. The atmosphere was charming and cozy. Our servers were very friendly and attentive. I will definitely be returning.
Organic, sustainable ingredients mean everything is fresh. Service very friendly, though can slow down when busy. Fresh seafood and shellfish, and hand made pasta like Nonna would make.
Only had a glass of wine but the atmosphere was cute and the food looked delicious
A bit noisy, but terrific stew
Amazing selection of high-end chocolates
Delicious seafood - a must-try Evanston experience
Not as good as Trattoria DOC, but great lasagna
My go to Italian restaurant in Evanston. Food is always great. The grilled calamari, Cacio e Pepe, and carbonara are my favorites. Service is always good.
For me everything was good, great food I would definitely go back again

Enjoyed having a haircut by a professional who knew how to cut my hair perfectly. The atmosphere was very comfortable and relaxing, with free snacks and beverages. The drive was well worth it. And the misses was happy with my cut. I recommend giving Le Peep Evanstona visit for your next haircut.
Wonderful ambience, lively but conversation possible, somewhat romantic even. Great service, wines, delicious food. Not outrageously expensive.
Neighborhood place for sure. But both times I have gone, people are very welcoming and I‚Äôm able to join any conversation. I like the atmosphere they create.

Had a good experience at Sketchbook this weekend. Beer was great (definitely get Snowy Owl) and tour was fun. For $8 you get a tour and 4 glasses of beer, which is pretty much amazing for the price! For an extra $2, you get to keep the glass.

After living in Evanston for more than a decade we finally patronized Campagnola. The service and food is excellent! It has a small menu which tells us that everything is freshly prepped. As a party of 5 we ordered 3 starters: Caesar salad (with an anchovy), grilled octopus, and bruschetta. For entrees we had grilled duck with polenta and a cherry reduction, short ribs with broccoli and creamy potatoes, a mushroom linguini, roasted chicken in a white wine reduction, and cellantani with tomatoes and mozzarella. For dessert we had lemon tart, chocolate mousse, and bread pudding. All the dishes were great. Even with a small menu (which is preferred), there was quite a variety of flavors from which to choose. This is a great place in south Evanston to treat yourself. They know how to handle a full dining room. All the service staff were well organized. Everything was served in proper order, with proper utensils, and good attention to details - even the water was kept full for everyone. Highly recommended!

Spoke with two older gentleman that highly recommended Kilwins and the ice cream was great but the service was bad, the staff didn‚Äôt know their own covid rules and my server Jeffery was pretty rude about it. I understand it was a busy day but there is no need to get frustrated with customers. I won‚Äôt be going back to Kilwins even though the ice cream was great but because of the bad service. The rest of the staff seemed polite but rushed.

The food was good but the bubble tea was impossible to drink with a straw. It kept on getting stuck. I tried to tell the lady but she made me feel stupid and bad about it, even offering a spoon. She said she'd refund me for the drink but I still got charged $21. All I had was 1 entree under $10 and an appetizer around $5. At that point I was too tired and irritated to argue so I paid and left. Used to be my favorite Thai spot years ago but things keep getting worse and worse. Won't be back.
The rib tips and sausage was Decent enough. Fries were 2 bags of cold inedible crinkle cuts. Fairly expensive.

Best Indo-Chinese restaurant in town! Lots of options to go for. Taste is very authentic and their HOT SAUCE is best. Staff was very good and service was pretty quick. They also offered us 15% discount because of ongoing construction. One thing to keep in mind their lunch menu is not available on Saturday and Sunday. They have not mentioned it anywhere. We went there for lunch menu but later found out that it isn‚Äôt available on weekends. They should mention it on their website.

Came on a Saturday night with friends. First thing you notice is the strong fish smell throughout the entire restaurant. After we ordered and received our drinks, the service was very poor. I was trying to get our waitress' attention for 15 minutes to get our checks. While my beer wasn't room temp, it certainly wasn't cold either. I ordered the bangers and mash. Very clearly from frozen, flavorless. The gravy was okay, hopefully that wasn't frozen too. It came with a side of beans that I am positively certain were from a can of Bush's Best. Extremely disappointing.
Such a sterile looking place. Clean .
We enjoyed a pizza exactly how the two of us ordered it. It's a very cozy atmosphere with both couches and tables to eat at.

I came here October 25, 2022 between 7-7:15pm to pick up an online order. The rude lady didn't even let me use the bathroom and was looking at me like I was an invader. I felt discriminated. If you aren't going to be welcoming to customers then don't work in a restaurant.

I heard someone say eating a delicious bowl of Mac and cheese is like a hug in your mouth. Well, I'd consider these empanadas to be like mini hugs. They are small but can be packed with big flavor. Surprisingly these snack size empanadas can fill you up. I usually order the Ground Beef, Malbec, and BBQ Chicken.
Best pizza in Evanston

This establishment is very wonderful. It's a nice and cozy place, with a peaceful yet comfortable atmosphere. The service is wonderful, and the food is amazing. The servers are very polite and quick to answer any questions you mave have about the menu. I would highly recommend this place as a hidden gem of Evanston.

Went in 12:05 to pick up a grubhub order that was to be ready at 12:10. Asked an employee at 12:20 when my order would be up? His response is, "I don't know!! A couple mins. "....smh, I guess it was just tooooo much work for him to go check on the name, so I decided to just unassign myself and take the acceptance hit. I'm sure a restaurant like this benefits hugely from delivery services since they advertise online orders only. My gripe is why is the order not ready for pick up at the pick up time us drivers are given?? I understand being short staffed or understaffed etc,etc. But for bloody sake, if you're understaffed and can't handle the work, then dont use the delivery service. The only ppl getting stiffed in this is the drivers. Anybody that grubhubs knows that you have to schedule blocks of time between 1 to 3 hrs. So imagine the frustration when you have to spend more than 30 mins out of the 3 hrs waiting for one order!!! Maybe in the future, be a little more understanding, and when asked by a person who is helping do your business and help it thrive, have a system in place where drivers can see how long an order will be from the scheduled pick up time given to them from the actual time you will have it ready!! Or just hire courteous ppl who can give a better answer than "I don't know!! A couple mins. "!!!

Very good, fresh sushi. We had sushi and ramen here and it was really good, probably the best in Evanston that we‚Äôve had. The dessert was beautiful and good, I recommend Exotic Bomba as something different and good. It‚Äôs fruit sorbet with which chocolate and just as good as it sounds.

Omg thank you thank you for opening picnic in Evanston! I can finally get a good quality legit salad loaded wit grains, lean protein, crunch, and flavor galore! I am in heaven! Every time I order I plan to only eat half and save half for the next day and sure enough I end up eating the whole thing. I tell everyone about this place - it is truly a gem. Don‚Äôt hesitate - you will want to lick the container clean!
A unique store with kitchen supplies, food and wine. Also home decor items. This is a great store for when you need inspiration for a gift. City parking garage across the street or street parking

The food is decent if a bit overly sweet. The portions are generous for a single meal (don't expect leftovers though) but the price is a bit high for what you get. It would get 3 stars except that they did not treat our family of 4 with 2 pleasant small children (a 3.5yr and a 6mo). At 6:30 pm on a Saturday, they made us wait 20 minutes to be seated while staring at empty tables in their side room (which was not completely empty or being reserved for an event) and then placed us in the loudest and busiest section of the restaurant while complaining about our stroller. Once we were seated, things went reasonably well but after we had finished eating, it took excessively long to get the check (which is problematic when you have kids beginning to get restless). I used to wait tables in a Chinese restaurant. I understand how staff scheduling and sections work. I can also understand that despite the liberal use of toys as decor, that a college town restaurant such as this isn't primary focused on catering to families. But, I also know that families with small children can be seen to with relatively few accommodations. That all said, they treated us as an imposition and not as welcome guests and the food is no where near good enough to justify another visit for us.
The √©clairs were simply delicious. My daughter loved them so much. We also had a French hot cocoa and that, too, was delicious. It may be my daughter's new go-to place.
It's pizza!

The atmosphere is very nice, cozy and upgraded and the food was excellent overall...but the service was awful! My husband ordered a non-alcoholic beer and was brought a full strength beer. The waitress poured it into a glass and took the bottle, so we didn't know until after he drank it; then when he ordered another one, the waitress realized what she had done. After profusely apologizing, she went and got another beer and glass, half poured it, left the bottle on the table and walked away. We looked at the bottle to make sure, and SHE DID IT AGAIN!!!! Absolutely unacceptable and negligent! The service was painfully slow...3 full hours on a weeknight without us ever telling her, we need a few more minutes, or we are content to sit and hang out. This place needs to get their act together!! VERY DISSATISFIED!
We went to try the ramen because our usual place was closed and this was the first result when searching for ramen in Evanston.
Recently found this place driving by and came back for dinner. The atmosphere is inviting, staff is friendly, and the food is delicious!

They really messed up my drive thru order last visit. I paid in cash then after going back and forth repeatedly asking me 3 times what I had ordered, then trying to upcharge me...And then- still got the order wrong. Put down the pipe guys!
I like the sushi here. Overall this is a good place. The donburi is a bit expensive for dinner. Lunch specials are great considering the price.
Absolutely phenomenal. My heart sang for the incredible food, service, and cocktails. If you are looking for outstanding DF Mexican food, go here, go here now!

Amazing bar staff with damn great hand crafted cocktails. The pizza is perfectly fired with incredible hand picked items. The chopped salad is perfect for sharing and their pasta dishes are to die for. If you haven't gone, make it a point to get there!

Craving a steak, i decided the next best affordable thing as having steak, steak as burgers! This chain is well known for their steakburgers and premium milkshakes. Their extensive menu is divided by: salads, melts, steakburgers, franks, chili, and kids meal.
Really good hot chocolate. I got the chicken sandwich. It looked good. The chicken strips were thin and the waffle fries were good. The service was good.
This is a nice hole in the wall located a short walk from the Evanston-Davis stop on the UP North and CTA Purple lines.
New design and new menu! The food is really good!!!

The pizza is ok. The service sucks.
The food comes out pretty quick.
I likely won't be going back.
Trying to go in on a Friday will get you a lot of disappointment.
Loved the authentic food and wonderful service. Enjoyed a dark and tan with bangers and mash, shepherd's pie, and fish and chips. Attentive service made the evening enjoyable.
First time trying it. Chicken curry and beef with the side of chimichurri sauce is fire
Food was ok. Not very oily.. So a plus. However, the chicken and the paneer dish had too much of food coloring. Wonder if it was to mask some other issue! Price was good for quantity.
That is a nice fast food places where everything is overflowing with flavour. Burgers are on a dry side, but not expensive. Kitchen might be buzy with Uber eats, but wait will not be long.

Great little place with very good food. Ambiance is upscale casual. Portions are not huge but the food is quite good. Pricing is a bit on the high side but sort of what you would expect for the area and the size of the restaurant which is somewhat small. Reservations are recommended. Pricing on the wine is a bit high and it adds to the overall cost of the meal. The appetizers were all great and the mains were all above average. I would say average price for 2 with appetizer mains and dessert is likely between $125 and $150 with wine. I will return but likely special event dining for our budget.

Large selection of their famous truffles as well as other upscale chocolates I haven't found anywhere outside of the boutique. The saleswomen were very helpful and offered their own recommendations. I will return to this location.
That Chipotle was bogus I paid for my ladies meal with cash and didn't get my correct change back and when asked about it I got hassled about my money from the staff

The positives are that the staff was very friendly and the Minestrone soup was good. However, a restaurant should be judged by the entrees and the the moussaka we ordered, was the worst moussaka I've ever had.
Frozen momo not made in house was served cold. Spices were not adequate. The only thing good was butter naan. Was not happy with food.
the bacon and dates wrapped up together was good. nice dishes in general. big place and not so crowded in lunchtime. octopus was also great. recomm.

This is one of the most authentic Chinese food in Evanston so we came here a lot. Just feel like the portion of each dish shrunk after pandemic while the taste is still nice. We were in a rush today and the waiter was very helpful in speed up our dishes. Thanks!
Oh I came back again after a week and that waiter remembered me, and asked if I am in rush this time. Lol. Cute
I love it . Tastes and friendly. This store have own style and cute.
Great

Usually restaurants with this kind of menu give me hesitation- like fish n chips, bangers n mash - because many of these dishes are terrible at many restaurants. Not this one. We had a delicious meal here last night and sat outside with a puppy!
The crispy salmon on risotto and peas was delicious and was my bangers n mash - very tasty and tender sausages and delicious gravy. The corned beef and cabbage was also very good.
Our only complaint was our server who was competent but absolutely no personality, and he disappeared after our meal was served and we had to go in and pay.
Great underground bar! Good food (in quantity and quality)

One of the only few places to get boba tea in Evanston. Standard tea with option to adjust sugar and ice level. They serve rolled ice cream. There are some board games but since the place is small, most just get the drinks to go.
I have to start off this review by clarifying that I am picky when it comes to ramen. For starters, I do not like pork broth and that is the base for most of the ramen at this restaurant.
Authentic delicious Belgian chocolates. Came here to buy a box of 35 Leonidas for a good friend. The pastries and French apple cake are just yummy.

Loved their huge variety of drinks and Smoothies. Hands down the best place for smoothies. The selection of toppings for the drinks is also amazing. Never seen something like that anywhere else. The food is absolutely delicious too! Good portion sizes.
Service has definitely improved just need a little quicker speed on the drive-thru especially when you order mobile
Credit to Chef Mark, Pete and Braulio who totally spoiled us with phenomenal food and attentive, professional service.

Great Burgers and Shakes

Hot Dogs Taste Swell when you Get One that's Not Soaking in The Juices A Long Time and When You Bite Into It 'Fowl Water Blues'.... My Only Beef is Long Soaked Dogs and Over The Top Grease Soaking The Bags Dripping Wet Burgers.
Check your food before u leave this location they give u what they think u should eat instead of what u actually order. Smh at least it‚Äôs always hot.

Affordable, efficient, and delicious! Came here for a quick bite to eat before going to The Music Box Theater for an event. We went in to order a few empanadas and then sat outside in their little patio. The food came out quickly on trays and we devoured them!

The service and staff here are fantastic! We got the dumplings which I thought had too much meat and did not care for the dough. We got the dry chili chicken which was very spicy and very good. Chicken fried rice was perfect with nice chicken breast pieces. Mango smoothy tasted like real mango and very well mixed. The menu is on the pricey side but they do have a lot of variety.
Savory Crust empanadas are better
Service took forever and gyros were terrible
Chicken tenders are incredible - can't tell they're not chicken!
It's Jimmy johns. End of story.
Best restaurant in Evanston - try the mantoo!
Overpriced but delicious sushi
Love the mint mojitos
Very dry kabob
Best salad ever, but they didn't deliver it with bread
Chocolate covered grapes are to die for
Inedible lasagna.
Not sure what the hype is about - inedible mushroom taco, stale steak, cold rice and beans. The chicken taco was good but overall very subpar. Also, no parking.

This place has a very nice and calm vibe, so I would totally recommend visiting it. Also, recommend making a reservation beforehand to save the wait time. We ordered a ton of food including fried rice, vegetable Momos, honey Chilli Potato, chili Garlic noodles, manchow soup, hot and sour soup, and chicken Manchurian. And it is some of the tastiest indo Chinese food we ate. The server was pretty nice and accommodated our additional request. However, besides ordering low-spicy chili garlic noodles, it was still pretty hot and difficult to eat. And we were not accommodated for that. The service was pretty slow which made our wait a little longer. For the price they offer, the quality is pretty much great. In the end, we ordered tiramisu and we loved it.
The chirashi is cheaply made with imitation crab, Tamago. The fish arrangement was haphazard. I won't be ordering it again. The tempura is good as was their Sapporo beer.

This was barely mediocre. I ordered General Tau's kitchen and got generic breaded chicken without the slightest taste of ginger. An orange sauce, obviously from a can, had been poured on so that it was indistinguishable from orange Szechuan chicken. Finally, the potstickers were inedible. If you know Chinese food, I wouldn't recommend this place.

Its a nice place to dine in downtown Evanston. Most of food menu consist sea foods though we can find other foods too. Vibe is superb. Food portion is not so much but we had pizza too so that was not issue. Pizza was good.

Nice place, typical spanish venue. The food is good quality, prompt service, nice people. Right price for the good quality food, wines and beers as well. Gluten free food available, suitable in case of coeliac disease.

Good: pork sausage, fantastic

Meh: brisket, I think I got a couple slices that were sitting around and a couple fresh slices. Its ok

Bad: I have never been to a BBQ place that doesn't sell by weight. The samplers force rib tips on you, if you want less than a full pound of meat you need to buy sandwiches.

This farm to table food is fantastic, and what happens to it between farm and table is magic. I was fortunate enough to taste it yesterday. What Jack Demar does to this fresh, healthful food before it gets to the table is artistry. The texture, color and taste combinations are amazing, but the layered, unique seasonings and dressings are something special. I really appreciate when someone bothers to strive for excellence in what they do! Jack Demar, you are there. Thank you.

This farm to table food is fantastic, and what happens to it between farm and table is magic. I was fortunate enough to taste it yesterday. What Jack Demar does to this fresh, healthful food before it gets to the table is artistry. The texture, color and taste combinations are amazing, but the layered, unique seasonings and dressings are something special. I really appreciate when someone bothers to strive for excellence in what they do! Jack Demar, you are there. Thank you.
It's decent. Sauces have very good flavor, but a little skimpy on the meat. Naan was good as was the paneer. I'd probably order again.

Went after football game. Hectic place, an indication the food's good and staff wants to turn tables. To describe the menu as "huge" would be an understatement, it might take 10 minutes to read the book-like selection of food and drink. Fun for groups. Splurge, and order a bunch of apps and entrees for your table, the food is reasonably priced for the portion size and quality.
Great addition to Evanston, szechuan style dishes to wet your lunch appetite. They offer lunch specials and regular menu items. The portions are huge can totally share.

So good! We tried the Ten Don, Spicy Albacore Maki, Shrimp Stir Fry, and House Sake. I love Japanese food and this didn't disappoint one bit. The service was excellent and the price was beyond fit for the quality. The meals came with salad and miso soup which was a nice bonus.

I really love the butter chicken here, as well as the naan. For the price of the lunch special, you get very good value. I also recommend the mango lassi. The restaurant is often understaffed, so service can be slow occasionally.

Oolong Milk Tea. With Herbal Jelly and 30% sugar. Maybe half if you need the fix. For 5 bucks, this alone beats out competitors and earns 5 stars. Add the variety, the cafe-style comfort with good lighting, and table games, there's no reason not to grab-n-go or stay a while. Oh look, the popcorn chicken isn't bad either....
Great burger

I really love their tea. Why 3 stars? Because their enforcement for the 6ft rules are nonexistent. They should really have a better system letting people in and out in such a TINY space. It was a lot of people inside, I chose ordering over the phone and wait until it was the less people possible to get in. They really should try the option of people ordering and paying by phone to walk in just to pick up quickly, not standing there!! And please keep your door open, you have to air it out!

Very promising spot on Evanston's culinary map! I went there yesterday with a friend, we ordered a lot of food (2 appetizers, 2 main dishes and drinks) and everything was delicious! The owners are super nice and welcoming, food is great and the prices are very fair as to the size and quality of the dishes. Highly recommended!

Food and atmosphere was okay. They had a good selection of tacos. I wish the potato taco and fish taco had some more flavor. We ordered 3 special cocktails. They were pretty unique and had a good flavor, but they could have been a little stronger IMO

In town on business and visited by myself. Unpleasant greeting kicked off my experience. Was seated closest to the bathroom despite a mostly open dining room. Waited for a while and three other tables showed up. Waitress addressed every other table before mine despite me being obviously ready. Ordered a Cesar salad and cheese lasagna. The lasagna was excellent. Cesar salad was sad, under dressed, two measly anchovies, excessive cheap box croutons. Honestly the lasagna made up for everything else. I might go back.
I travel quite a bit as a pilot. This was the worst crawfish etouffee I have ever eaten. Took a few bites and didn't eat the rest. Calamari was tough. Wife's mashed potatoes and salmon seemed fine.

Dined in, very attentive service! Really liked having them confirm everything in the order, including the spice level. Water refills were aplenty which certainly helps if you get something spicy. We always get the string beans, and will be back again soon!

Their bento boxes are tasty and have good portions. I have tried 2 of them which included rice, corn, broccoli and chicken. I ordered teriyaki chicken the 1st time that I went to this place. It was tasty and well cooked. The 2nd time I went there, I ordered popcorn chicken and it was a good as well.
I am very satisfied with each meal that I have eaten there because they are hearty and worth the price.

Such good food. The tacos were awesome, I tried 3 kinds. Before the tacos even came I couldn't stop eating their salsas - they were so delicious I almost ruined my appetite with chips. The staff were very attentive and I didn't have to wait for anything. My only regret is that my stomach isn't larger to eat more tacos.

Tasty vegetarian options! I especially like their Nepalese dishes and their chai tea. Also, their rice pudding is very flavorful with a lot of cloves. It‚Äôs not like any rice pudding I‚Äôve had on Devon. Wheelchair accessible so you can bring guests who need accommodation.
Incredible chocolate selection here.
We are chocolate lovers and tried 3 different flavor chocolate cakes. They are all awesome. Will try more in the future.
Delicious tacos! The chips that they serve with salsa at the beginning is actually warm. As if they just came fresh from the fryer!
Pretty cool place. The tacos are tasty, although a little pricier than some competitors. The building is entirely framed in steel making it a bit of a Farraday cage. Which plays with Wi-Fi reception.

I use to go to Dave‚Äôs Italian Kitchen quite often when it was on Chicago Ave, but after they closed then reopened in the new location I simply forgot all about them. My friend reminded me of the Spinach Ricotta Pie, which is the only thing we use to get there because we didn‚Äôt have much luck with many of the other items on their menu and it was delicious. We went there this past Saturday and both ordered the dish. I‚Äôm not sure if the owners are the same, but I sure know the dish was not. It‚Äôs now served in a bowl with a thicker mushroom sauce, more like gravy, poured on top. The sauce was hot but both of our pies were cold in the center and barley lukewarm on the edges. I honestly think they just heated up the mushroom sauce and poured it on top of unheated pies. The pie was swimming in the sauce, which most time I‚Äôd be happy about. However, the sauce was SO lemony that I could barely eat it. I like lemon but this was really unbalanced. I think both of us ate about 1/4 pie. We asked for to-go boxes because the server was really nice and neither one of us wanted to make her feel bad. We both tossed it in the trash when we got home. Needless to say, we won‚Äôt be going back.
Overpriced

Im new to the area for work and really wanted BBQ. My pulled pork was very dry. My ‚Äúgumbo‚Äù was mostly just rice even after stirring (pictured below). The greens were fine but too much vinegar. The grits were my favorite part. They also forgot utensils which would have been nice since i am at work.

Try the jerk chicken. It's like a party in your mouth! The savory well-seasoned meat and sauce with the rice and beans with a side of cabbage and fried plantains is a complete meal sure to satisfy the hungriest person. I will surely eat here again.

Rude customer service. I placed an order on the app to pick up my bubble tea in the Evanston store. I went in the store to wait for my order to be made, and the lady with short straight hair working at the time asked what I wanted so I told her I placed the order in the app already. She yelled at me and said I need to let her know next time because she doesn‚Äôt know that I ordered on the app. The tea I received was also too sweet (I regularly order the oolong milk tea with less sugar and noticed the difference). I will not be returning to this location again because of the unprofessional customer service.

The food is good but their business practice is extremely unethical and not right! They do not give itemized receipt and automatically charge you for over 20% of gratuity. They give you the bill to sign and there‚Äôs still a place for you to tip. If I did not pay attention to the total amount they charged me, I could have tipped over 35%. Is this even legal? They should stop this unethical, ridiculous practice IMMEDIATELY.
Got macarons for all my students here for final exams - pricey, but the kids loved it

I ate carry out from here three nights in a row. I love Szechuan food and this was no exception. Each meal was huge; I ate almost no rice and still could barely finish the entree.
Chongqing popcorn chicken: it's a huge meal even if you don't eat the abundant red chilis. Don't be scared off by the 3/3 hot rating. The chicken is wonderfully spicy but if you evade the chilis it seemed more like a 2/3.
House special pork stir fry was actually a bit hot for me-- I couldn't make it through the jalapenos (those aren't bell pepper!). The pork by itself was great.
The Kung Pao has tasty chicken, lots of peanuts, some chilis, and slices of ginger. It was very tasty although it has no Szechuan pepper.
A bit pricy but they definitely have the best sushi in town.

Might be the worst salad I have ever had. I literally spit out the tomatoes. They were spoiled. Threw the salad in the garbage. The other dish was super salty and the flavors and textures didn't work for me. I lived and studied in Italy and while I don't expect real Italian food in American restaurants, I do expect fresh healthy food. Isn't that the soul of Italian food? Ambience is lovely. I would give it five stars for ambience. Good place for a drink.

I normally LOVE Chipotle, but the food tasted funny, so I didn't finish my Burrito bowl. I can only assume that since I arrived right after they opened up for the day, that maybe they were still doing safety/service checks. The flavors also hadn't been added to the soft drink machine, so I had soda water.

Me and my friend waited 30 mins after getting seated and no one came to take our order. People that were seated after us had their order taken right away. No one looked like they knew what they were doing. The server that was supposed to be for our table said she wasn't even aware we were her table. The workers were gathered around the bar, talking. And they didn‚Äôt even apologize for this behavior. The level of incompetence from the workers was absolutely unacceptable.This was the worst experience I‚Äôve ever had in any restaurant.

We have been coming here for a couple years , good food , drinks and ambience !
This visit was even better, right as we sat down we realized we had to leave to help our friends with a favor that would take 45 minutes ... but were worried there would be a long wait when we came back . When we informed our waiter of the conflict we were in they said, don‚Äôt worry go help your friend we will make sure when you come back you get The first available table !  We came back and true to their word we were seated right away even with many people waiting ahead of us  .
Now that‚Äôs great service !

I‚Äôm so disappointed with this restaurant. My latest order was a horrible experience. It took 1 hour and 45 minutes for my meal to be delivered. After an hour of waiting, I called because I had to leave my home in 30 minutes. They told me it would be another 35 minutes, so I told them I needed to cancel because I would no longer be home at the time they could deliver. They then said it was almost pulled together and that they would have it to me in 20 minutes. However, the reality was that it took 45 more minutes before it was delivered and had to sit on my cold front porch till I got home. Clearly, they lied about the status of my food. If they had just told the truth and allowed me to cancel, they would have kept a regular customer. Instead, they chose to lie to keep the order, so they‚Äôve lost my future business. To add to the bad experience, they didn‚Äôt make good on the free delivery and fee desert they had promoted in an email.

Tasty sushi and very kind waiters. I had great lunch .
Just one thing that soy souse its kind weird and so many carton boxes around place
Will come back

Omg what a great experience. The food was incredible the service astounding. Now I went on a Groupon ,dont laugh at the groupon, now the only bad thing is they shouldve listed in the fine print about having to pay 40 for a tip is mandatory and you will need to factor that in bc wuth the tip and drinks it was almost an additional 100 yes for the tip n drinks. N I only had two. So I gave it a like but had I known about that ahead of time wouldve loved it.

This is my second time eating at this place. First time was during lunch 4 years ago. This time was during dinner. Every dish we tried was a flavorful and unique twist on Thai cuisine. Desserts were also delicious. Overall, I would highly recommend this place to anyone looking for a unique dining experience. The staff was friendly and attentive.

Excellent Japanese cuisine specifically if you're into Nigiri, Shashmi, and quality rolls. Service was excellent as well. I'd give it five stars if the pricing wasn't quite so hefty. Still very good for a quiet lunch or dinner with the whole family.

Today we ordered Thru door dash for our first time from this restaurant. Appalling customer service over trying to get half of our order corrected. Was told to deal with it Thru the app. Door dash is unwilling to issue any refund. 1/2 of our order is compromised. 1 item missing, one the wrong item and one has a hair in it. The employees on the phone each time I called were polite and apologetic, stated the manager is off duty and when they txt him he said nothing can be done. It is crazy how door dash adds so many fees to a customer ,charges so much for service and I am sure the restaurant gets charged fees for their service too and then neither are able to refund or send the correct food. I was using a gift card today, I am so disappointed in the poor quality of care, bad business ethics and just down right unacceptable food service and management. I would say don't spend your money here and get your empanadas from someplace else. One very disappointed and disgusted customer and I'm sure the 3 people who were in this order with me would agree as no one got what we paid allot for.

Order the short ribs got something else with the bone in.
Waste of money.
Seafood ramen was good.
Pretty spicy.

I‚Äôm extremely satisfied with my order. The fish is really fresh. Kaki sunomo is the best!! If you like sashimi, I strongly recommended sashimi dinner. I‚Äôd eat here everyday, if I could. Also, I really appreciate the attentive staff always offering Edamame as complimentary. They are all really nice. Great food!! I definitely come back here again!!

I got the papaya salad, fried tofu, and crab cakes. I really liked the crab cakes and salad, and I appreciated them having gluten free options clearly labeled on the menu. I think the tofu would have been tastier if it weren‚Äôt room temp. The staff was very friendly and helpful.

The only thing that would have made my experience it better is if the fried tofu and crab cakes weren‚Äôt near room temperature. I called in my order at 5 from my car outside the restaurant and was told to come pick up the order in 30-45 minutes. I went inside to pick up at 525 and sat for a few moments while they finished putting my order together. I then took it right out to my car parked right outside the restaurant to eat, so it seems like it should have been hot.
As a local Real Estate Advisor, I pride myself on knowing all of the wonderful things my community has to offer.
Overpriced macarons

From the truffle to the shashika. The guy is so amazing and nice. I always feel self conscious because I am not jewishish and I am a tattoo artist covered in tattoos. He has made me and my wife feel welcome thank you souch bud.

Love the knot. Excellent service, delicious pub food. Great curry chips. Love the good, but modest beer selection and variety of whiskeys. The staff is always nice and service is fast. Parking can be an issue, but it's worth it if you enjoy bluegrass, pub food, and beers. If you are in Evanston and want a pretty authentic Irish pub experience, then this is your place.

Discovered this place through an ad, and it did not disappoint! We are used to traveling far away to satisfy our indo chinese cravings. This place conveniently located in Evanston, serving the Chicago community, Skokie, lincolnwood and Morton Grove residents is a treat for indo chinese lovers. We started off with some chicken corn soup. The soup was of proper consistency and tasted well. The appetizer was fire cracker chicken, it's slightly crunchy, and spicy!! When I say spicy, it's spicy!! We got chicken indo Chino as an entree which has a black bean vase save, it was meaty, and it had lots of gravy. Our entree was paired with hakka noodles and Schezwan fried rice which went phenomenally well. For our vegetarian options we got spicy egg plant and vegetable gold coins, which tasted nothing less than gold! They have many flavorful vegetarian options also and there is also a vast mocktails menu. Parking is easy to find as well. Overall, I will be visiting again and trying different items on the menu.

Delicious, authentic, traditional Italian. The service is amazing and the food is the best. My favorite is the cacio e pepe.I love that they have half portions, too.
Fair warning: They tend to close early, often before their posted hours. We were refused service at 8:40 one night. On the plus side, they are now open for lunch!

Stone pot kept the soon dubu jigae warm through the meal + great tofu. Tteokbokki was a little on the sweeter side, but still really good (better with some rice). Highlight of the meal was the budae jigae! Wish the portion was slightly bigger, though.

One of the best barbecue restaurants
In Evanston Illinois five star ‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê
Every thing is good on the many blessings to all the staff  Carmel cake amazing

While the food was fine, I brought 9 people into an empty restaurant. 65 minutes after placing our order, while other tables had been served, paid, and had new customers seated, we had nothing. When I asked the waiter why, he said the manager said to put our order in last because we were a large table; the manager confirmed this. 75 minutes after arriving we were served, without apology. I know 9 people who will not eat here again.
I ordered for delivery 2 veggie bowls and was delivered only 1 veggie bowl that was not what I ordered

It should be a five but I specifically went there for a malt. Last time I was here was pre-pandemic, so... things have changed and I haven't kept up with them. My boring chocolate shake was delish and the guy at the window had a great smile (it's nice to see smiles).
Really nice staff. Made my friend and I the last two bubble teas before closing because we all the way from the south suburbs. Their bubble tea is definitely some of the best bubble tea I've had.
Really nice folks. Great pub food. And a pint of Guinness poured properly.

First time at Soban, but many many Korean restaurants around the entire Chicago area. My standard first time item is (yuk guy Jeng) Yukgaejang, which is a spicy soup with shredded beef, green onions and green bean sprouts with glass noodles. It is hot and spicy, and it helps me determine if the food is authentic. My wife always eats the Dolsot Bibimbap, rice crispy in a stone bowl and cooked veggies and a fried egg, and a selection of different meats,shrimp, tofu, etc.
Both dishes were outstanding and served hot and delicious.
It's beer bro
Amazing Service and even better sweets. Keith and Conrad are a dynamic duo of customer service and entertainment that light up my day every time I stop in, easily one of the best stops in Evanston.

Best Jamaican (Caribbean) restaurant in Chicago. Very authentic place. Come for the food, ignore the loud music and patrons. Limited seating, I sat for 45 minutes - left alone to eat and observe. One Love!

We were at the Evanston area to celebrate the 4th. We came across this shop from Yelp while looking for asian dessert places. I have to admit this shop surprised me in a VERY good way. The tea selections are amazing, plus it has brown sugar milk or tea latte options (it‚Äôs very popular now after cheese tea). The bobas were chewy and had brown sugar taste. We really enjoyed our drinks. Service was fast and place was clean.

First time trying it out. Personally, not worth it for me. I ordered the SoCal wrap with a side salad (came out to about $15 before taxes and tip). The wrap was so soggy, despite me ordering it without the cilantro lime dressing. The side salad was fine, but I ordered with no tomatoes and it came on it. The carrot miso dressing was delicious though! However, I can‚Äôt see myself returning here.

I think it was the most overpriced burger I have ever had. The quality of their burgers is not even close to justify their prices. Initially I thought those prices were for combos. Not only that, I personally think their burgers are not good at all. Overcooked/burned, dry and small. This was my first visit to epic burger and I don't think it convinced me to go there again.

Came here because it's right under my apartment. Very good and inexpensive coffee and other drinks. Great prices for food. The egg and cheese hand pie was very tasty and filling, good quick breakfast. Great outdoor seating and cool collection of books and boardgames to borrow while you eat.

he avocado was bad - my girlfriend and I both had it and had horrible stomachaches after. Besides that, it was extremely overpriced and mediocre diner food. The avocado toast was completely bland and unimpressive despite its 10 dollar price tag, as was the BLT with its 15 dollar price tag. Both can be made at home for half the price and twice the quality. The bossa nova covers of pop songs are as nauseating as the food.

Cute place. Decent selection of board games with all the modern classics. I enjoy the vibe - lots of kids here, which makes me happy because they have somewhere to hang out in this sleepy senior town. I also appreciate that they are open relatively late by Evanston standards. The food was basic but is good to snack on while you play.

Delicious Japanese food. We ordered the chicken bento (pictured), the agedashi tofu, and the oyako don. All of it was very flavorful and at a reasonable price. I am happy to support a long-standing family owned local business!
Tasty and affordable korean food and super fast service. The bibimbop is really good! I got it with gochujang sauce, highly recommended!

Very good ramen and takoyaki. The atmosphere is nice as well: the Japanese music is fun without being annoying (no Jpop) and they play old Japanese movies and TV shows on a screen in the back. Highly recommend the spicy miso ramen.
Ordered on DoorDash. Very very expensive comparing to its very small portion. The uni we ordered was not fresh at all. It smells bad. Would never order again. Overprice and poor quality food.
Amazing beer, great atmosphere
Disgusting
Amazing beer

Sadly this place is bad for its business practice of adding 20% on to checks no matter the amount of people. I was there by myself and they added 20%. I objected because they‚Äôre taking away my right to tip what I felt was fair for the service. The owner who was there that day screamed at me saying ‚Äúhow am I suppose to make money‚Äù? I was shocked. She ended up taking the 20% off the bill because I stood my ground. I told her she lost a customer and I never returned. Shoddy is an understatement!!
Horrible food, no flavor at all

Consistently amazing food and great service. Their spin on urban Thai fusion using authentic flavors provides an unique culinary experience that changed my understand of Thai flavors and ingredients. I Have never had a dish there I did not enjoy, which is rare considering I typically hate veggies and found myself loving all the food (even the ones that are vegetarian). Leave behind whatever preconceptions of Thai food from the westernized dishes that you typically see in a fast food or strip mall Thai restaurant. Their complex flavors using traditional ingredients and artistic presentation produces a fine dining experience in a casual setting. The staff are extremely friendly, providing exceptional service whenever we dine there. Great food, welcoming ambiance, and friendly service. Can‚Äôt ask for more and eagerly plan to return for more.

I normally love trying new bubble tea places but I just ordered the cocoa cream wow and it is disgusting. I‚Äôm not sure if it was made improperly or if this is actually supposed to be this salty. I‚Äôve tried mixing it with my straw and it‚Äôs just not good. I saw the drink on a sign and ordered the drink as is (no substitution) and this has no sweetness to it.
I have been at this establishment a couple times and lets just sayy experiences were not good. Where is management?

We ordered the meat lasagne which is $18. The portion is small, bland and you can‚Äôt find the three different types of meat.
Also ordered a pizza with mushroom and sausage. Tasted like a premade crust which they added cooked sausage and mushroom and heated it. It was also bland and flavourless. Would not recommend and would not pay these prices for the food we received.
The restaurant is huge and a lot of people overflowing during evening. The food is good quality. I liked their pasta and chicken and also tilapia fish. The mashed potatoes are tasty too!
The food was good and the amount was enough. I ordered veg rolls and duck meat. I will like the duck more well cooked, apart from that it's fine.

I was a little wary coming in because the prices seemed really high and they didn't have any of the "classic" Thai dishes you'd find at other restaurants. I got the Jumbo Lump Blue Crab Meat. It was very filling and its presentation really pleased the millennial in me. This probably wouldn't be my go-to Thai place but I would definitely come back for a nicer occasio
Good place to go, variety of greek dishes and good service.

Tasty burgers that make it worth the visit. Lots of people getting a milkshake as well but i couldn't fit one in! Chips were hand cut and well seasoned.

Is it the best burger joint in evanston? Based on solely the patty, i think Bat17 wins in flavor. Nevertheless, a great vibe, friendly staff and fast service. I would go again.

I just left this wonderful establishment, and wow is all I can say. From the art to the food, this is my favorite restaurant to open in Evanston in a while! As a lifelong Etown resident, it is a breath of fresh air to see a true, authentic, indigenous Mexican restaurant. I sat at the bar and was greeted incredibly graciously by Jen, who explained to me in-depth the details (Zentli means Corn in Spanish), ingredients, and meaning of the entire menu, which is inspired directly from the chefs' mother and father.

Great pricing for amazing food, family like environment, with kind and attentive staff. I had the Flautas Palmar but will be back to try to entire menu haha. Would definitely recommend to anyone who loves Mexican food!

Do yourself a favor and visit this lovely restaurant Clarke's Off Campus. I experienced the Chicken Caprice sandwich and those awesome fries. Fresh condiments stacked on top a beautiful and delightful taste. The owner truly cares about your experience. Highly recommend!

This is my second visit. Ordered different things. Offerings are consistent and delicious. Service is friendly and helpful. Tom Yum soup w/ Tofu was amazing. Can‚Äôt wait to go back again. Staple of downtown Evanston!

Hecky‚Äôs Barbecue has been a Evanston staple for years . I decided to have them for lunch again one day and it was good . I ordered the ‚Äúmutt‚Äù and it delivered. The mutt is two smoked wings , rib tips ,one hot link and fries. The wings could‚Äôve been cooked a little longer but was still tasty and the sauce isn‚Äôt my favorite but everything else was good . Hecky‚Äôs always come through when I have a taste for bbq.
Recommend: Chili oil dumplings

Ordered boba tea for my daughter‚Äôs birthday. I was able to order it it in larger portions (for 50 people) at a great price too. It was such a hit at the party and the drinks and tapioca were delicious. I have to say they have it down with their tapioca being so soft and the perfect texture. Love this location! Also the owner took care of us and went above and beyond to make sure we had everything we needed.

Short walk from my hotel, prompt service, but for the price, you could at least get my order right. Cashier specifically asked me what type of Mayo I wanted, but then didn‚Äôt get any Mayo at all. Specified that I wanted extra pickle, got 2 pickles. For a $17 burger, I just wanted it the way I ordered it.

Maybe I just ordered wrong but I was very disappointed. The hot tea was delivered cold,though the replacement was fine. The ribs with black bean sauce were all fat, the curdled egg with pork was tasteless. No one asked how my food was.

I love the food here although I usually have my 'go to' Spicy Basil Leaves with chicken. At lunch, comes with salad or baby egg rolls and I always get the crispy egg rolls. They come out warm with a sweet sauce.The decor is fun and you can usually find parking nearby. The only con is that they automatically add the gratuity and don't mention it so some unknowingly double up. I look forward trying more items.
Always bustling. Small taproom but friendly people and staff make it work.
The peking duck!
This is my go-to-place for Chinese food. So authentic! We live in Chicago proper, but still drive up to Evanston to eat here often. Their beef dish is amazing, so tender and well spiced. A real gem!

Food 4 stars
Environnement 5 stars
Staff 5 stars
Price $$$/$$$$ (because of small portion)
Overall 4 stars

We ordered five entree and two appetizers for five people: coconut poached seafood, amish chicken, two beef dishes, crab rice noodle, crabcake bites, and the peanut chicken bites. The food are amazing. We love all of them, especially the chicken bite and crab rice noodle. The service is kinda lack though, considering the price is more expensive than other thai restaurants.
Not up to standard
Still not up to standard
Not up to standard

The Alcove Evanston was a wonderful experience for us. The service was slow, as every other review suggested, but let's be compassionate; they may be short-staffed. Staff were courteous, professional and hardworking. The food was excellent. We will definitely return.

Food is good, but EVERY time I order the salad, they forget the vinaigrette. Then, they take NO RESPONSIBILITY for the mistake if it is delivered by a delivery service. THEY pack the meal so, how is it Grubhub's fault, not theirs? This has happened MANY times, not just once.
Definitely recommend this place for great movie snacks, including European chocolate. They have gluten-free snacks, too (especially blue corn torilla chips with flaxseed).

Unlike most boba places, this place serves classic milk tea that you would find in Asia. Dining area is the size of a coffee shop, and friendly staff. Prices are good too, although make sure to bring cash unless you plan on buying at least $8 worth of drinks in order to use credit.

Amazing! I'm so happy to see the Spinach ricotta cheese pie with mushroom lemon butter sauce still on the menu and one of my favorites
The creamy garlic salad dressing is the best I've ever had

Good but not great.
I expected more for place that opened for over 30 years. I saw head chef cutting frozen tuna that used for nigiri. Most of sashimi I ordered was frozen. Cook food was good but so outdated for this day. Only I like is how bright inside and good services.

I recommend Sarah‚Äôs Brick Oven. We had wonderful pomodori specialty pizza (good crust), tasty classic Shakshuka, delicious Jerusalem salad, falafel (average) in pita. Service was quick. Pizza had eggplant, garlic, black olives, feta, red onion, mushroom, topped after baking with arugula (as I had it in Europe
Delicious chicken tenders make kids happy
Kids love the burger and fries here
Super fun spot for brunch with the family
All the ramens are fancy - kids just wanted noodles in broth and they couldn't accomodate
Not kid-friendly - they threatened to kick us out for being too loud
Delicious pancakes - the kids loved them
Kids loved the tacos!
No kids menu, won't come back
Plushie wall is adorable!
Best pizza for the whole family

Ok.. I admit my pic game isn‚Äôt the best; however, I must say this was the best dinner I‚Äôve had in a long long time!!
I had the beet salad as the starter and the roasted duck entre√© with cherry sauce.
100% absolutely delicious!!
Good stuff. Their braised pork belly is lovely but very filling, and their other menu options do not at all disappoint. It can sometimes get packed on Fridays, so plan ahead.

I usually don‚Äôt write bad reviews but I just ordered takeout and bit into RAW beef‚Ä¶um..it also tasted powdery so I‚Äôm pretty sure the cornstarch also didn‚Äôt dissolve/cook through properly‚Ä¶the dish was the flat noodles with beef‚Ä¶really disappointed because I heard good things about this place :/ Maybe it was just a bad night but raw beef?!? not slay

My wife and I went to get an appetizer and some drinks. It was about 2pm and there was only two other tables of patrons there. I ordered a Bloody Mary and my wife a Margarita, both top menu items and you‚Äôll see that on their photos. We waited 40 minutes to get the drinks and we were already severed and done with our appetizer by then. We were planning to go for breakfast the next day but the experience we had for such a small order made us change our minds on that.

I usually go to restaurants on Devon Avenue when I go out for Indian food, but my fiance lives in Evanston so we tried this place instead. I enjoyed the food and the service was also fine. It's your typical Indian place, with a wide variety of dishes and regional food. The prices and portions are also about what you would expect for a place like this. I will definitely be going back there.

Queer friendly, affordable, and delicious French patisserie! My partner and I stopped here for the first time on our way home randomly and we are so glad we did so! We both got croissant sandwiches and drip coffee, they were so tasty and incredibly cheap! I highly recommend this place. Food comes out fast and is packaged nicely. *Note that if you are immunocomrpiesed and or disabled, the space inside is very small and can be crowded with of course unmasked people and may not provide accessible space for mobility aids.* Can not wait to go back! $17 for two high end croissant sandwiches and two drip coffee's, I believe this patisserie will become a weekly favorite of ours!

Great lunch special. Highly recommended. I would definitely return next time I'm in the area!! The interior has very little charm or style and it's very dim inside, but the food is so good you don't notice.

The service is great. For example, when we didn't notice the QR code menu option, our server brought paper menus and asked if we'd like to order with her or via our phones. It was nice to have the options explained that way, and we opted for the "traditional" paper menu order since we were keeping our phones in our pockets (hence, sadly, no photos of the food).
Recommend: Lemongrass chicken noodles
Spicy Miso was a 10/10
Lovely atmosphere, great service & the margaritas, carne asada & lamb tacos were all magnificent! Seriously good food! Can‚Äôt wait to go back and bring some friends!

Very neat and nice restaurant with friendly staff. The food is really good and the prices decent. I had a lovely dinner experience. I would recommend this place to anyone looking for good nepali food.

Recently dined at The Alcove -- first time in person since they remodeled and changed their name. The new design is beautiful, elegant and understated. Lovely little hidden spot.
Primarily a pizza place or was , hence the name "Brick Oven". We usually frequent for breakfast and have the shakshuka.

Regret not checking out prior Korean place. So was ready to have some coffee/nosh at 10:30 with a friend at the new incarnation, Papa Bop..  SURPRISE they open at 11 a.m.!And they do not serve coffee...at all!  But they do offer three teas, the honey citrus was super.  Also menu is limited and only Korean dishes.  And the bowl was wonderful. Had a small cup of delicious white miso soup first and then the basic be bop bowl with veggies, beef, sprouts, rice and more incl a fried egg! The beef is amazing. The fried veggie dumplings are divine. All the little tasting dishes are pure authentic and home made

Awesome food and ambience. Got their lunch special of lamb shish kabab and chicken barg. Lamb was EXCELLENT, melted in the mouth, juicy and tender with good flavors. Chicken was good too but loved lamb better. The hummus and salad that came with it tasted really good too. Portions were perfect to the price. The staff was very helpful to choose our order; this was our first time here. The afghani decor and atmosphere was very neat and peaceful. They have few dedicated parking spot. Definitely coming back again!

Update: I started getting this feeling that a lot of the food here is starting taste dry or stiff. The french toast edges are mostly stiff and the sausage and potatoes were also dry on the outside, making it harder to cut and chew.
Went here for dinner on weekend. The decor and the interior is very nice, about as nice as I‚Äôve seen for an Afghani restaurant!

Had an enjoyable 5 course set meal. As the name implies, their specialty is seafood. Had the ocean trout as the entr√©e and it was prepared very well. It was silky smooth and the sauce was a great pairing. The service was nice but not above average for the price point. It is a nice conformable restaurant that is worth trying.

One of the best BBQ joints around. I mean, who else can say they've been cited by the EPA? Ribs are meaty and come off the bone. Little dry on my last trip, and the price is creeping up, but hey, we all got bills to pay
Amazing BBQ
Totally YUM experience. Amazing ice creams and candy! Delicous hot chocolate. Must visit in Evanston

This place is a hidden gem in Evanston. This was my first time wandering downtown Evanston and we noticed this cute French bakery. Too bad due to covid you aren‚Äôt allowed to sit indoors because the inside is cute. The pastries look amazing and they have a wide selection of warm drinks. They do have outdoor seating but it is very chilly out. We got a pear tart and a caramel apple dome pastery. I highly recommend trying the caramel apple dome! Would definitely come back to try more pastries and support an awesome small business!

have been ordering from Panino's for years. I order today for family that is in town. I receive a pizza that is all messed up. Cheese and sauce all over. I call and they apologize for the pizza and promise to send another pizza.

So many options I love it but the worst part is trying to decide which one to eat. I love getting their stir fried noodles and pho. The second time I went the pho broth was not as good but still good but on sweeter side. Bubble tea is very good here.

This place deserves over 5 stars. Incredible service, food, flavors, ambience, authenticity, and everything in between! We did the tasting menu and left stuffed.

We had very good experience. Food was very good. Ambience is also nice. Their service was also good and quick. We had chilli garlic noodles and cauliflower manchurian gravy. Noodles were really good. Manchurian was also fine. They also served plane rice with the manchurian which was surprise for us as they did not mention it in menu. They have good vegetarian options. Their portion size is also very good.
This place is great! Their portions are good, the stuffed French toast and side of sausages were delightful!
Service was courteous. Appetizers pretty standard. Masala was quite disappointing. Food was bland only slight hint of wonderful spices we were hoping for.
I worked with Chef Pascal to create a custom vegan high tea menu for my girlfriend's party, and he was outstanding! He took a lot of time to speak with me and meet our needs.

We had one of the best Italian food we ever had. Everything what we ate was really amazing, full of textures and flavors. Our server was very knowledgeable and polite. Right away we ordered a dry martini with olives staffed with blue cheese.

Service was good but the food was disappointing to say the least. Probably the most flavorless food I've ever eaten. We were really trying to find a good authentic Japanese restaurant and was excited to see all the good reviews. However, the food was definitely not great. The teriyaki chicken and beef tasted like they boiled the chicken and beef and thrown sauce on top. It was placed on top of a wet iceberg lettuce with a side of old boiled carrots. Gomae ai was just flavorless sesame paste on top. The side salad (mostly iceberg lettuce) was also drenched with water making the lackluster dressing even more bland. Sashimi was ok but definitely not the freshest fish. Overall, food was definitely below average and not worth the price. Gave it an extra star for service but would probably be closer new to one star if based on food alone.

Awesome place for bubble/milk teas, and all sorts of other fun, colorful, assorted drinks. Very fast, up-front, and direct customer service. They even have Lactaid (lactose-free milk) for lactose-intolerant individuals (look for the name 'Wow' Tea). Inside, there are two kiosks to order from if paying with a card, but if you can also order in person too at the counter.... Always popular with Northwestern students & neighborhood people alike so expect a bit of a wait, but so worth it. You will be happy you did.
This was the first time going to Soban and all I can say...I will be going again! Some of the best food I have ever had!
Love boba forever!
Their rolled ice cream is very light, not too sweet not too soft either. The teas taste good and you'll be good on a hot day with a large size.
Bubble - well made, it's chewy like how it suppose to. Anyone complaints meaning they dunno what a true bubble taste like.

The souvlaki meat (both pork and chicken) were very flavorful and juicy. The Maria fries had lemon sauce and were covered with crumbled feta. Service was quick and efficient. Parking is metered on the street outside. Cash only. There's an ATM next door.
he bbq sauce is a tad cloying, and overwhelming. i‚Äôd almost get the meal dry with the bbq sayer as a dip.
Ordered delivery, everything was still heat hot but it was all lacking flavor. Pot stickers were large but very gummy.
They offer a lot of indo- chinese options. The main course was decent. But they should improve a lot on their appetizers and their service.

Ordered two large cheese pizzas for take out from here on Sunday afternoon. They quoted a 30 minute wait time. That time was misquoted to us, but not by more than maybe ten minutes. The timing was long forgotten, once we saw and tasted that pizza! DELICIOUS üòã The staff was very friendly and accommodating. We'd have given them a Perfect 5 STARS, were it not for unfortunate timing. We will Definitely be returning for our Pizza cravings.
I love the honey milk tea from this place. The tapioca is sweet vs bland at other tea places.

Staff and owner very accommodating. Even though we were running late we got seated right away. waiter very friendly . Didn't feel like we were rushed or anything. Great service and food exceptionally tasty and fresh. Bread out of this world.

It wasn't bad a little pricy alot of thier food was bland like the pork belly taco I couldn't even taste the pork belly, and the duck chorizo the chorizo seasoning was over powering the duck you couldn't even taste. Also do not expect it to be spicy if your used to some spicy foods

Hands down the best steak I've ever had. Excellent service, historic atmosphere, and the food to match it. This is truly a hidden Evanston gem. Planning on going here for any special occasion and perhaps to the bar itself for an occasional drink!

One of the best restaurants in Evanston. Great food and live music, especially around St. Patrick's Day. Their Chicken/Fish & Chips are great especially with the Guinness BBQ Sauce! The staff is always friendly and welcoming. A place for staff lunches or casual late night outing.

Excellent dining experience. We had a good mix and maybe because we are Asians, the food is not hot (chilli) enough. Haha. But still great to have some of these food. Worth it especially when you don't have such food for a long time.

honestly try another italian place, unless you like runny pasta :/

Anekdin por Kolkata Chinese! Crispy baby corn was

Soooooo great. Love the IPA selection, servers, concept, art, and I bought a t-shirt! Rage on

he space feels intimate and warm despite it being a high ceiling, concrete floored barn‚Ä¶ great design. Also manages to feel casual and elegant at the same time, with both the design and ambience.
Very nice and cozy place. A good selection of cocktails and wines. Quality meats and meals. Servers and staff are pleasent and helpful. Will be glad to come back.
Went for a date night and it did not disappoint. Great Australian wagyu with brussel sprouts and perfectly cooked Bone in rib eye. Service was great and the waiter was extremely knowledgeable.

This place never fails to deliver. We cater for our team of 75 and they knock it out of the park every time. I come here all the time and get the rib tips, easily the best in Chicago. Will keep coming back here time and time again.

I almost forgot to mention the friendly, courteous staff, and adorable seating areas.

Exquisite cafe. I was pleasantly surprised to find a Parisian cafe like this in the Midwest. Very refreshing to see since the US is sorely lacking independent bakeries. The quiche was delectable and the croissants were perfect. Prepare for a wait, it seems pretty popular.

4th time eating at Kansaku. As always, very warm and welcoming environment. Kansaku offers very tasty appetizers along with excellent maki rolls (lobster king and Carnival)!! Service was quick and friendly. Definitely coming back again!
